2. Check Serviceability.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | Bundle Availability Service doesn't return the All-In-One flatrates (FI3:AI1,FM5:AI1)
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 

Channel: MHV

Cable PCAT: V2450_2025_01_00_032

The MHV portal calls the Bundle Availability Service to correct GigaKombi products if both cable and mobile orders are in the basket.

We observed that the Bundle Availability Service is returning the wrong responses. Specifically, it does not return the All-In-One flatrates anymore (for example, FI3:AI1, FM5:AI1).

 

{+}Actual result{+}: 

We send this request body to the Bundle Eligiblity Service:
{

"offerContainer": [

{

"productLineCategory": "Cable_Internet_Phone",

"processContext": "ACQ",

"tariff": "2BV:N12",

"cartItemSkus": [

"2BV:N12",

"69K",

"GB9",

"V3K"

],

"serviceAddress": {

"country": null,

"city": "M\u00fcnchen",

"locality": "Sendling-Westpark",

"streetName": "Sachsenkamstr.",

}

},

{

"processContext": "ACQ",

"KGM2MOS",

"K5GFREE",

],

"country": null,

"streetName": "Sachsenkamstr.",

"streetNr": "13",

"streetNrSuffix": "",

"addressId": "6211810"

}

}

]

}

 

We receive the response:
OfferContainers:
Cable_Internet_Phone (ACQ): serviceLineId NEW, partyId , tariff 2BV:N12, nonOsfSkus [], offerings [
EXISTING: 2BV:N12 (GigaZuhause BV 500/50 Kabel, 1.-12. Monat 19,99 € [2BV:N12]),
EXISTING: VSA:N24(Vodafone Station [VSA:N24]),
EXISTING: RNRN (Neuanschluss [RNRN]),
EXISTING: HO1:000 (Option Homespot 0,00 € [HO1:000]),
EXISTING: PAS (SuperWLAN [PAS]),
EXISTING: 69K (Gutschrift Bereitstellungsentgelt [69K]),
EXISTING: KB9 (Vodafone TV Connect Start BV [KB9]),
EXISTING: GB9 (Rabatt TV Kabelanschluss [GB9]),
EXISTING: OF5:B00 (Festnetz-Flatrate (Bundle) [OF5:B00]),
EXISTING: FM4:B00 (National Mobile-Flat (Bundle) [FM4:B00]),
EXISTING: 3K6 (Bereitstellungsentgelt [3K6]),
EXISTING: V3K (Versandkosten 3P [V3K]),
ADD: VA1 (GigaKombi Marker Internet & Phone [VA1]),
ADD: VM2 (GigaKombi Vorteil Mobile-Flat [VM2]),
DROP: FI3 (Mobile & International-Flat Standardangebot [FI3])],
Mobile_PostPaid (ACQ): serviceLineId , partyId , tariff KGM2MOS, nonOsfSkus [], offerings [
EXISTING: KGM2MOS (GigaMobil M ohne Smartphone),
EXISTING: K5GFREE (5G-Option (kostenfrei)),
EXISTING: KMESSAGE (Vodafone-Message),
EXISTING: KPROMO015 (Anschlusspreisbefreiung (PROMO015)),
EXISTING: KPROMO013 (Aktion: Unlimited for All - unbegrenztes Datenvolumen (PROMO013)),
EXISTING: KPROMO011 (Testpromo ¿ keine Buchung möglich),
ADD: KGKMOBDATA (GigaKombi - Datenvorteil),
ADD: KVFAIO2MRK (GigaKombi),
ADD: KVFGSAIOHKaDV_8_4034 (GigaKombi Gutschrift)]

 

+Expected result:+

The relevant problem lies in the ADD and DROP section of the cable products.

We expect
ADD: VA1 (GigaKombi Marker Internet & Phone [VA1]),
ADD: VM2 (GigaKombi Vorteil Mobile-Flat [VM2]),
*{*}ADD: FI3:AI1{*}*

DROP: FI3 (Mobile & International-Flat Standardangebot [FI3])],

But actually FI3:AI1 is missing.

Our tests show that this was still working correctly on November 14{^}th{^}, but not anymore on November 26{^}th{^}.

A similar problem appeared in the OSF portal, it might be related: [[OS-65730] OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | Mobile Flats with AI1 Promotion (Gigakombi) are not shown in the Shopping Cart and Extended Shopping Cart anymore and change to different Mobile Flat with AI1 Promotion is not possible - Vodafone Global Jira|https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOS-65730&data=05%7C02%7CAnton.Ustimenko%40vodafone.com%7C186f4a24753c4dbb0ad408dd1453bdb5%7C68283f3b84874c86adb3a5228f18b893%7C0%7C0%7C638689072096056926%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=uzhMXTuUurSFmjpaLpkTrXGrCjcwPpWpCYQ1%2BnxW1UA%3D&reserved=0]

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | Mobile Flats with AI1 Promotion (Gigakombi) are not shown in the Shopping Cart and Extended Shopping Cart anymore and change to different Mobile Flat with AI1 Promotion is not possible
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 

Channel: Telesales + Retail

Cable PCAT: V2450_2025_01_00_032

 

 

*Please note:* 
 # on ACC2 the bug does not appear
 # when selecting "[FI3] Mobile & International-Flat GigaKombi" under "Optionen" after adding GigaKombi, [FI3:AI1] Mobile & International-Flat GigaKombi is displayed in the Shopping Cart and Extended Shopping Cart – > *OK*

!image-2024-12-01-08-48-48-061.png!

3. when selecting "[FI4] Mobile & International-Allnet-Flat GigaKombi" under "Optionen" after adding GigaKombi, "[FI4:AI1\] Mobile & International-Allnet-Flat GigaKombi" is displayed in the Shopping Cart and Extended Shopping Cart – > *OK*

*!image-2024-12-01-08-50-30-433.png!*

4. ** The configuration on Cable side is correct:  !image-2024-12-01-09-01-19-062.png!

 

{+}Actual result{+}: Mobile Flats with AI1 Promotion (Gigakombi) are not shown in the Shopping Cart anymore and change to different Mobile Flat with AI1 Promotion is not possible

 

+Expected result:+ Mobile Flats with AI1 Promotion (Gigakombi) should be shown in the Shopping Cart and change to different Mobile Flat with AI1 Promotion should be possible

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load for a Cable address on ACC1, e.g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Angebote mit Vertrag"
 * select a GigaKombi eligible MOB tariff, e. g.: "[KGM2LOS] GigaMobil L SIM only"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select a GigaKombi eligible KIP tariff, e. g.: "[2BV:N12] GigaZuhause 500 Kabel, 1.-12. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on the button "Gigakombi erstellen"

– > section for selecting a Mobile Flat is missing – > NOT OK

Expected: !image-2024-12-01-08-28-20-234.png!

Actual:

!image-2024-12-01-08-28-36-861.png!

– > "[VA1] Vodafone GigaKombi Angebot Red Internet & Phone Cable" and "[VM2] GigaKombi Gutschrift Mobile-Flat" are added to the Shopping Cart, but FM5:AI1 is misssing:

 

!image-2024-12-01-08-30-03-052.png!
 * continue with the order until the Order Overview

– > "[FM5:AI1] Mobile & Euro-Flat plus GigaKombi" is displayed – > *OK*

*!image-2024-12-01-08-36-26-296.png!*
 * click on the button "Vertragszusammenfassung senden"
 * click on the button "Drucken"

– > "[FM5:AI1] Mobile & Euro-Flat plus GigaKombi" is displayed in the Contract Summary – > *OK*

*!image-2024-12-01-08-38-21-227.png!*
 * compete the order

OSF Order ID: 916797

– > In IAV "[FM5:AI1] Mobile & Euro-Flat plus GigaKombi" is displayed – > *OK*

IAV Weborder ID: 8476872

column904:
04/Dec/24 3:41 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;Last comment from Frederick in PSTBUG:

When investigating this bug it only occured on the ACC1 and not the ACC2.
The cable posting rules are out of the question, as they are not even executed when clicking the gigakombi button.

We also checked the relevant input files on cable and mobile pcat side (Bundles.xml).
Diffing the involved cable products easily showed no significant changes.
The relevant bundle rule in this case is GK1a gigakombi bundle rule that has not changed in a very long time.
In particular I specifically checked exactly the imported version of the Bundles.xml.
This is why I wrote that this is an OSF issue.

Diving into OSFs backend shows that the problem is indeed not the input, but rather how it was processed and came out on the other side.

Bug was not reproducible on ACC2
!image-2024-12-03-20-52-17-907.png!

but occured on ACC1
!image-2024-12-03-20-40-43-675.png!

Probably OSF is best adviced to check the colons in their backend.;;;

column897:
15/Nov/24 12:58 PM;satish.dhere1@vodafone.com;As per Z_PRT00147947A

 
When the SetOrder with  status "CUSTOMER_CREATED" received 
 
The order line status updates should be like below 
1) InProgress-FulfillmentStarted  2) Set Order "CUSTOMER_CREATED"" received -> Order Status change to  InProgress-DocArchiving 
 
After Archiving/Metadata Update Completion  order status should change back to  InProgress-FulfillmentStarted  .
 
And Final Status Update should be Completed-Success after receiving FInal Set Order "ORDER_COMPLETED" from BE(FN/DSL)
 
 
Now our observation is that: for point 2) Set Order "CUSTOMER_CREATED"" received -> Order Status change to  InProgress-DocArchiving ----------for our order, this condition is not working
PushorderStatus - InProgress-DocArchiving is not triggered by OGW
 ;;;

column900:
11/Nov/24 6:57 PM;darshan.ramlingapa@vodafone.com;Hello All,



If the issue occurs again, it might be helpful to check the following two fields in the order tracking tool. 

!image-2024-11-11-18-55-34-893.png!

Both fields must be in state OK. If not, the completed event has not been posted. Multiple asynchronous processes are involved in the posting process of the order status. These asynchronous processes might take some time and have some internal recovery mechanism in case of problems. So it can happen that this process takes some time.

If the issue occures, I would propose to first check the ordertracking tool. If both fields mentioned before are in state Active, then I would suggest to wait a bit and see if the issue cures itself.;;;

column921:
18/Dec/24 7:39 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,
i think this is because the new implementation of cr 604.
OGW is trying to call oneDms.
if there is an empty response then OGW will check the table: ogw_error_handler with this error: OGWERR-0099.
now it will try the numbers of times according to the value in the table: under max retry times.

in out case 24.
so first try it is not counting because it not retry, its the first time we calling the service.
1 + 24 = 25 times;;;

we can check like so:
select * from ogw_error_handler where error_code = 'OGWERR-0099'.
this insert was deliver as part of wave 9.2;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | ACC1/IT | OGW triggering Fulfillment Started after completed Success post Fast Search Sky ticket resolution for DSL orders
column41:
We have observed that OGW is triggering Fulfillment Started after completed Success even after failing Sky ticket of Fast Search for DSL orders.

 

*Test Data:*

Order ID: 889251, 889259

OGW order ID: 1891035, 1891044

Barcode ID: VDE5601891035, VDE5601891044

Env: ACC1/IT

 

*Step to reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius with Telesales channel.

2)Configure DSL Package.

3)Submit order.

4)Verify OneDMS fast search interface triggered empty responses for 24 instances.

5) ( parallelly BE processing is done and received "Order completed" from the BE ) need to consider this condition too 

5)Check the Sky ticket is generated and fail the ticket using Sky tool to skip the Archiving 
6) check if push order status "complete success  " is triggered towards OMNIUS 

7) OMNIUS should display order completed status on FE

 

 

*Actual Result:* OGW is triggering Fulfillment Started after completed Success post Fast Search Sky ticket resolution (ticket failed to skip Archiving) for DSL orders and hence OMNIUS is still showing the InProgress status on FE 

*Expected Result:* OGW should not trigger Fulfillment Started after resuming the sky ticket (Failed to skip archiving) and should trigger only push order  status "Completed success " towards OMNIUS  (Here we are considering BE status is also received completed success)
column346: DSL order status will still be in progress in Omnius frontend even after skipping the archiving flow by failing the Fast search sky ticket which impacts the overall status of the order in Omnius.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | ACC1 | OS-47654 | Sliding charges calculation is not shown correctly in Extended Shopping Cart
column41:
We are performing below scenario for Device financing
 * Mobile customer having a tariff A and a SOC B with e.g. 12 month runtime
 * After a while e.g. in month 5 he is changing his contract with an ILS
 * Customer gets an additional runtime SOC C e.g. 3 month

What we should see in the CS is the following:
 * Month 1-3, Tariff price + SOC C + SOC B
 * Month 4-7, Tariff + SOC B
 * Month 8 .., Tariff price only

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to omnius in Telesales/Retail channel.
 # Perform mobile customer search
 # add new soc which is having certain duration
 # verify sliding charges in extended shopping cart.

 

Expected result: Sliding charges should be displayed correctly

Actual result: sliding charges is not displayed correctly.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | In the Access Details the value "Nach Rechnungslegung löschen" in the field "Verbindungsdaten speichern" is displayed incorrect
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 (test2b)

Channel: Telesales + Retail

Cable PCAT: V2420_2024_10_00_061

 

*Please note:* 
 * the issue also appears on ACC2

!image-2024-10-15-19-18-11-338.png!

 

{+}Actual result{+}: In the Access Details the value "Nach Rechnungslegung löschen" in the field "Verbindungsdaten speichern" is displayed incorrect for VKD and Unity Media orders

 

+Expected result:+ In the Access Details the value "Nach Rechnungslegung löschen" in the field "Verbindungsdaten speichern" should be displayed correct for VKD and Unity Media orders

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load any Cable address on ACC1, e. g.: "Von-Galen-Str. 63, 51063 Köln"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: "[5BV:N12] GigaZuhause 50 Kabel, 1.-12. Monat 9,99 €"
 * continue with the order until the Access Details
 * select the value "Nach Rechnungslegung löschen" in the field "Verbindungsdaten speichern"

!image-2024-10-15-18-58-16-526.png!
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > Instead of the value "Nach Rechnungslegung löschen", the value "Speichern (Gesetzliche Frist)" is displayed – > *NOT OK*

!image-2024-10-15-18-59-45-374.png!
 * create the order

– > OSF Order ID: 889305

In IAV the data is displayed correct:

IAV Weborder ID: 6133930

!image-2024-10-15-19-08-53-673.png!
column346: In the Access Details the value "Nach Rechnungslegung löschen" in the field "Verbindungsdaten speichern" is displayed incorrect in OSF - just a display issue, the value is provided correct to the Cable Backend, but it is confusing for the agent - same issue also appears on ACC2

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | ACC1/IT | Fast search output is not received from OneDMS for DSL orders
column41:
We have observed that Fast search is triggered but Fast search output is not received from OneDMS for DSL orders.

 

*Test Data:*

Order ID: 888205, 888427

OGW order ID: 1889518, 1889851

Barcode ID: VDE5601889518, VDE5601889851

Env: ACC1/IT

 

*Step to reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius with Telesales channel.

2)Configure DSL Package.

3)Submit order.

4)Verify OneDMS fast search request in OGW.

5)Verify OneDMS fast search output in OGW.

 

*Actual Result:* Fast search output is not received from OneDMS for DSL orders.

*Expected Result:* Fast search output should be received from OneDMS for DSL order.

column41:

{+}Actual result{+}: Selfinstall is displayed as red on addresses where ABK = yes AND Selfinstall = yes

 

+Expected result:+ Selfinstall should be displayed as green on addresses where ABK = yes AND Selfinstall = yes

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

column897:
18/Oct/24 2:45 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
 
Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 

As we analyzed further with VF reporter and BA and identified that this is an expected behavior on OSE side. OSE will show Self Install → *Red* if we receive the node *selbstInstallationKz* with value {*}N{*}, *Green* when the *selbstInstallationKz* value on this node is *J.*

If on MAMAs response we have value J and OGW send the value as N on OIL. Then this has to be checked with OGW why we have wrong mapping on OGW.

Thanks;;;

column1: On-Hold | OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | A Sky ticket is created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 

Channel: Telesales + Retail

DSL PCAT: OSF-20241027_Version_391_FN_2024_10_10

Test data: 001956928712

 

*Please note:* this bug is already in Production

 

{+}Actual result{+}: A Sky ticket is created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory – > Missing *refComponentId in Component for SecureNet*

 

+Expected result:+ No Sky ticket should be created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * search for a DSL customer with SecureNet in the inventory on ACC1, e.g.: 001956928712
 * click on "Meine Produkte >> DSL package >> Paket ändern"
 * select a new DSL tariff, e. g.: "[R708.2000000020-24] GigaZuhause 250 DSL"
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > "[I1414ISN01] Secure Net+" and "[GS_SN_3x3_99[br]] 3 Monate Rabatt auf Secure Net+" stay in the inventory – > *OK*

!image-2024-10-15-10-42-19-205.png!
 * create the order

OSF Order ID: 889055

– > Sky Ticket is created

*Service Name*
FNSubmitOrder
 
*Error Code*
SIDCOM-ERROR
 
*Error Description*
An error was encountered while invoking FN-CreateFNPOrder WS. Details [Error_Code: SIDCOM-ERROR, Error_Message: ERROR COM0000: Sorted SOM is INVALID! nullcvc-complex-type.4: Attribute 'ID' must appear on element 'secureNet'., Error_Type: , Error_Sevirity: , Error_Information: ]

 

[~marco.abraham01@vodafone.com] has already analyzed the bug:

 
 * at ILS no information about SecureNet is provided to the Backend (Also at a cancellation of SecureNet nothing os provided to the Backend)

 * missing refComponentId in Component for SecureNet in RetrieveCustomerInfo - Mode2 logs

column1: SPN-OPT-000142343| OSF | ACC1 & ACC3 | IT | CS and CD are taking time to generate on OM side and stuck on SPP state
column41:
We have observed that OM is taking too long to respond which is leading to delay of generation of CS-CD.  It is taking more that 15 min to process in IT ROM.

This was observed on 09.10. and 10.10. after installation of Hotfix on OM on 8.10.

TestData :

ACC1:
Telesales - 885931/Vertragszusammenfassung Nr. 11749027
Retail - 885935/Vertragszusammenfassung Nr. 11749153

 ACC3: 

Telesales- 446937/ Vertragszusammenfassung Nr. 11753454

Retail- 446951/Vertragszusammenfassung  Nr. 11754082

 

Since 11.10. the orders stuck completely at initial state, and it takes up to 1,5 hours to process. 

!image-2024-10-17-08-19-25-920.png!

 

This is observed for all consumers from OM, not only for OSF. Additionally several documents are processed slowly, maybe because the CS document generation is stuck and the other documents have less priority

Additionally we have checked the load, but there is not more load than before 8.10. observed

column591: the main problem was that a password had been deleted from the configuration artifact because it was no longer required. However, during the deployment, there is a pipeline step that replaces all password placeholders with the actual value from the encrypted password store. This step failed because it expected the password placeholder to be present, but could not find it anymore. As a consequence, many applications could not start, because there is a sanity check that the password should be replaced."

column901:
10/Oct/24 5:24 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;Root cause analysis from Portals Solution:

"the main problem was that a password had been deleted from the configuration artifact because it was no longer required. However, during the deployment, there is a pipeline step that replaces all password placeholders with the actual value from the encrypted password store. This step failed because it expected the password placeholder to be present, but could not find it anymore. As a consequence, many applications could not start, because there is a sanity check that the password should be replaced.";;;
column902: 11/Oct/24 11:37 AM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Issue is Resolved, Hence closing this ticket.;;;

2) Check the obtained barcode in COM for 1270 status.

3) Perform BE processing in OPM the next day.

4) Check for 1499, 1290 statuses in COM DB.

5) Verify in OGW that Fulfillment Started is triggered after Completed Success is received.

 

*Test Details:*

Order ID: 884819, Barcode: VDE7601884598

Env: IT

 

*Actual Result:* Orders are not successful in FE due to mentioned behavior in OGW. 

*Expected Result:* Orders should get successful E2E without any issue.

column41:

Please find attached error message:
  !image-2024-10-09-15-12-50-681.png|thumbnail! 

*Steps to reproduce:*

Step3: search result displayed which are partially masked

Step6: click on it
Step7: MTAN authentication window should ask for mTAN code sent to phonenumber(when generate MTAN is successfull)
Step8: Enter the code and submit (Validate MTAN is triggered)
Step9: Validate MTAN is successfull
Step10: After succesful mTAN validation prospect lead should be open under product intrest tab in readble formate
Step11: open one Product Interest
Step12: Check under ""Product Interests"" tab in Customer 360 View and cable lead should be present and click on convert button from three dots menu
Step13: click on convert button

*Actual Result*: Getting service not available error while converting cable lead into order

*Expected result*: Once click on convert button page should be moved to the configurator

Yes that service not available error message is expected in case that cable product is not available on that address but which address we used during lead creation on that address cable product is available even if it's through an error service not available and once click on convert button service avaibility should be successful and page should move to configuration

column899:
10/Oct/24 5:29 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment - 
 
 
HI [~nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com] 

Based on further discussion with VF and @Sarabjeet it is identified that the serviceability we do manually via serviceability bar goes in 2 step 1 validate address happens based on response we received we trigger the CheckServicibality with complete address details.

But in case of convert lead we depend on address details received as part of search lead response and these details are not complete in the above case, which resulted in different CheckServicibality response. And on this case cable and cable tv were not available to service.

Thanks;;;
column900: 10/Oct/24 8:12 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Internally checking this issue.;;;
column901:
10/Oct/24 8:57 PM;nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com;Hello [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com][~sunilkumar.cm@vodafone.com]

We have checked and compare both response for Cable and DSL where we cannot see any different for Response. And yes it is working for DSL lead.

Please see attached lead search request/response for DSL and cable.

As per the below design stories we cannot see any difference in response.

OS-52121
OS-52122;;;
column902:
11/Oct/24 12:03 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
Hi [~nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com] ,

As we discussed the lead search response we get address details to trigger the CheckServiceibility and it may be possible to get search response with same address. Then OSE will use the address received on lead search response. In this case we trigger the check serviceability using the same address for both DSL or Cable covert lead and serviceability response is same in both cases. But that response allow change to DSL lead only and not Cable. Because Cable availability is false for the address we triggered check serviceibility.

Thanks;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | In a special use case it is possible to create an order with an unchanged TV package
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 (test2b)

Channel: Telesales, Retail

Cable PCAT version: V2420_2024_10_00_039

Test customer: 935098503

 

*Please note:*
 * the bug also  appear on ACC2 (test4b)
 * !image-2024-10-07-10-44-36-132.png!
 * For DSL and KIP and KUD and MOB it is not possible to continue with an empty package (see screenshots below)
 * For new-activation KIP + empty TV package it is also not possible to continue (see screenshot below)
 * For ILS TV tariff change it is also not possible to continue with an empty package (see screenshot below)
 * When creating an order with an empty TV package (Customer ID: 201535623; OSF Order ID: 883933; IAV Weborder ID: 6129501) no error appears. The TV package is ignored and not added to the Weborder in IAV

!image-2024-10-07-11-33-41-535.png!

!image-2024-10-07-11-33-17-435.png!

 

 

{+}Actual result{+}: In a special use case it is possible to create an order with an unchanged TV package

 

+Expected result:+ It should not be possible to create an order with an unchanged TV package

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load a Cable TV + KIP customer: 935098503
 * Click on “Meine Produkte >> KIP package >> Paket ändern“
 * Click on „Optionen“
 * Select any option, e. g.: “[OHH] Option HomeBox (Fritz!Box 6670)”
 * Click on “Meine Produkte >> TV KAD package (TV.001) >> Paket ändern“
 * *Do not book anything*
 * Click on the button „Weiter“

– > It is possible to create the order with an empty package in the Shopping Cart

!image-2024-10-07-10-44-26-348.png!

 

For DSL and KIP and KUD and MOB it is not possible to continue with an empty package

!image-2024-10-07-10-46-07-480.png!

!image-2024-10-07-10-46-15-692.png!

!image-2024-10-07-10-46-27-229.png!

!image-2024-10-07-10-46-44-254.png!

 

For new-activation KIP + empty TV package it is also not possible to continue

!image-2024-10-07-10-47-26-984.png!

For ILS TV tariff change it is also not possible to continue with an empty package

Customer: 935120852

 
 * Load an existing Cable customer with TV, e. g.: 935120852
 * Click on “Meine Produkte >> TV KAD package (TV.001) >> Paket ändern“
 * Select any new TV tariff, e. g.: “[CTWUP2] Vodafone GigaTV Cable inklusive Vodafone Premium”

– > „[KASWAP] Tausch des Kabelanschlusses“ (change of KAA) is preselected, that’s why the KAA package is added automatically to the Shopping Cart -> *OK*
 * Deselect „[KASWAP] Tausch des Kabelanschlusses“
 * *Do not book anything* -> KAA package is still in the Shopping Cart but without any change
 * {*}{{*}}click on the button "Weiter"

– > an error message is displayed and it is not possible to create the order – > *OK*

!image-2024-10-07-10-52-13-250.png!
column346: In a special use case it is possible to create an order with an empty TV package - same behavior in production near environment -- > no business impact
column591:
OSF is checking that there is no change in a package, but because of the interfaces between OSF/IBP order, etc (they are mostly based on products), there are also technical marker products which are not booked at the end but they are needed for the transmission of information from OSF to IBP.
If such a marker is booked, then the behaviour described in the bug appears. On Cable side this is not problematic.

According to SubmitOrder request logs. there is product sku (WESTATUSSI) added for TV package in shopping cart. which allow to submit the order. Refer the CommercialDetails node.

column918:
24/Dec/24 3:22 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;Hi,

 

we have discussed this defect together with Gaurab from Amdocs in one of the sessions, last week, in which we analysed E2E the expected behaviour and discussed some defects.

Also Waldemar and Michael Heller were involved.

 

1. What I miss in this error description is the EXACT activities, that the agent/tester has done.

my assumption is:  the agent has selected the unsharp sim swap (which is a possibility in Retail, that will disappear with the esim Push Epic, but is still available if the permission for insert sim_serial_number is set (I think)

so..  question:  did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

 

Because:

IF Agent selects UNSHARP SIMSWAP, 

THEN SubmitOrder.SIMCARD = E (as it always was)

and... OGW is triggered to send the emails when SIMCARD =E

(so.. this is not correct)

 

AS AGREED WITH GAURAB :

Amdocs will change/improve the software:

OGW will not only check for SIMCARD = E,  but will also check whether the NEW_SIM_SERIAL_NUMBER is not populated.

only then the emails will be sent;;;
column920:
30/Dec/24 5:25 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;-> did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

Hello [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com] In both cases, Email is getting triggered, As the parameter SIMSWAP reason is always handed over to OGW with the value VR (Unsharp) even if the agent has selected Sharp (VS) in front end.

Please find below screenshot from submit order request.

!image-2024-12-30-17-19-16-405.png|width=485,height=600!;;;
column921: 30/Dec/24 9:12 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com]  please check the comment from Ajay and let us know if anything still unclear ;;;
column922: 08/Jan/25 12:04 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;Hi [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com]  could you please check & share your observations.;;;
column923:
13/Jan/25 8:46 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;So final outcome  (my understanding)

Summary: 
 * works as (wrongly) designed
 * Amdocs will fix this without the need of a Change Request
 ** OGW will not only check:  is SIMTYPE E, in order to trigger the emails, BUT also check if the SIMNumber is empty

 

Details:

RETAIL channel; blocking permissions set:
 * agent must therefore insert SIM number (instead of SIMTYPE) AND
 * agent has possiblity to select Sharp vs unsharp simswap 

Omnius sends in submit Order
 * SIMYPE E, because agent has selected unsharp SIMSWAP (not clear to me, but it looks like Omnius also sends SIMTYPE E, if the agent selected sharp SIMSWAP, if I understand the comments right). 
 * SIMSERIAL number (because Agent has inserted a (physical) SIMnumber 

OGW triggers 5910 and/or 5930 email although the agent has inserted a (physical)  sim number

 

Solution: Even if Omnius sends SIMTYPE E,  OGW must also check, if a SIMNumber is provided  in submitOrder.  if the simnumber is empty, only then trigger the emails 

-->  as aligned with Gaurab some weeks ago

 

 ;;;

[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 

 this topic needs to discuss with VF design team,

For me this is not a defect.

Basically in mobile package usecase SubmitOrder xml. AddressDetails node pointing to SubscriberDetail node. So it can easily identifying the pointer for AddressDetail node to OrderlineDetail.

Where in cable/dsl usecase, there is no subscriber then how it was done in past to identifying AddressDetail node to OrderlineDetail.

And there was an agreement that regardless of if order contains single or multiple cable package the AddressDetails must pointing to CustomerDetail node. where these address can or can’t identical. this behavior is since wave1

Whereas Delivery Details node point to Address Details seq. and this looks to me working as per design.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Mobile SOHO RV Prolongation Telesales orders are failing in KIAS.
column41:
We have performed Mobile SOHO Business RV Prolongation scenario in Telesales channel, In this scenario, We have observed, Create Contract service is failing with “Request not allowed for Subscriber under skeleton BAN” error message.

Please find below Request and Response:
{code:java}
<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap=http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope xmlns:bas=http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Schema/Common/BaseTypes-ESB-001 xmlns:cus=http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Service/EAI/Letter/CustomerDocument/CustomerDocument-003>
   <soap:Header>
      <bas:controllObject>
         <!--<bas:auditObject>
            <bas:user>cz00eai4</bas:user>
         </bas:auditObject>-->
         <!--Optional:-->
         <bas:retryObject>
            <!--Optional:-->
         </bas:retryObject>
      </bas:controllObject>
      <bas:appMonDetailsStrict>
         <bas:bpId>OGW1727516574369</bas:bpId>
         <bas:bpName>CustomerDocument:ContractLetterRequest</bas:bpName>
         <bas:boId>OGW1727516574369</bas:boId>
         <bas:callingApp>OGW</bas:callingApp>
         <bas:initiator>OMNIUS</bas:initiator>
      </bas:appMonDetailsStrict>
   </soap:Header>
   <soap:Body>
      <cus:ContractLetterRequestRequest>
         <!--Optional:-->
         <cus:ban>107196772</cus:ban>
         <cus:subscriberNumber>GSM1722393747</cus:subscriberNumber>
         <cus:callerId>O</cus:callerId>
      </cus:ContractLetterRequestRequest>
   </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>
{code}
{code:java}
<ROOT type='java.lang.String'>An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-CreateContract WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI003988, Error_Message: Request not allowed for Subscriber under skeleton BAN., Error_Type: Functional, Error_Sevirity: E, Error_Information:  Request not allowed for Subscriber under skeleton BAN., Backend Error Code: 1652]  </ROOT>{code}
Test data: 1876468

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Search existing Mobile Business RV Customer which is eligible for Prolongation.
 # Check Prolongation eligibility on front end and Select Hardware in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout and Submit order.
 # SubsidizedHandsetProlongationRequest received successful response from KIAS.
 # OGW trigger ContractLetterRequest towards KIAS.
 # KIAS Return error message in response - Request not allowed for Subscriber under skeleton BAN.

Actual: Mobile SOHO RV Telesales orders are failing in KIAS with request not allowed for Subscriber under skeleton BAN error message for ContractLetterRequest.

Expected: ContractLetterRequest should not trigger for SOHO RV customers as KIAS does not allow to update Subscriber under skeleton BAN.

column897: 03/Oct/24 12:46 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Schedule call with VF BA to discuss this issue.;;;
column898:
04/Oct/24 3:59 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Send mail to Business Team: [~andrea.allmenroeder@vodafone.com] [~janine.hesshaus@vodafone.com] [~jan.beuss1@vodafone.com] for their confirmation on this functionality.

We have identified Prolongation issue in Wave9.1 Acceptance Test for Skeleton Business customers where OGW is calling “CustomerDocument:ContractLetterRequest” call towards KIAS but KIAS is not accepting this call and returning following error back to OGW -> Request not allowed for Subscriber under skeleton BAN, Due to this issue order are getting stuck in OGW and OGW opening SKY ticket for same order. Can you please check from Business side that Is this “ContractLetter” Required for Skeleton BAN?
If Yes -> KIAS needs to accept this request.If No -> OGW needs to remove this call for Skeleton customers. 

Please find below JIRA ticket for Reference (Request and Response logs are present in ticket).

Reference Ticket ID: [OS-62672] OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Mobile SOHO RV Prolongation Telesales orders are failing in KIAS. - Vodafone Global Jira

*Business Impact: SOHO Business RV Prolongation orders will not be completed E2E in Telesales channel.*

Agent can only see customer 360 view details and cannot perform change or prolongation activity in Telesales channel.

OGW order_id: 1875862(ILS), 1875076(new ACQ)

Orders are not successful in orderline status 

*Expected Result:*
Orders should successful in orderline status

there is an US related to CR562. VFDED1FTS-3562 identified to say VVL is allow for dunning customer in Omnius.

column906:
08/Oct/24 8:29 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I took a look from cable side, the implementation for this rule has not changed since it was implemented.
The rule looks like follows:
{code:java}
- identifier: "informAboutFtthAvailability"
  description: "Display a message to inform the agent that they should talk to the customer about the FTTH availability"
  condition: "availability.HasTechnology(null, 1, 'FTTH-L2-BSA', 'GRUEN,GRUEN_GRAU,GELB', '(ACCESS_SUPPLIER;OXC)')"
  title: "WICHTIGER Buchungshinweis - OXG Glasfaserverfügbarkeit"
  text: "An dieser Adresse bitte auf FTTH beraten! Für DSL/KIP gilt: Downgrades nur für Wechselgarantie, Upgrades nur auf FTTH erlaubt. Neukunde nur mit max. BB 50 erlaubt."
  processContext: [ "ILSBLU", "MIGCOC", "MOVE", "ACQ" ]
  packageType: "CABLE_INTERNET_PHONE"
  portals: [ "OFT", "HA" ] {code}
Relevant place in the repository: https://github.vodafone.com/VFDE-Portals/ProductSetup/blob/main/input/omniusData/Cable_Messages.yaml#L302

The condition was provided to us by [~marco.abraham01@vodafone.com] during the discussion of the implementation quite some time ago in this comment: [https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-51716?focusedId=3110733&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-3110733]

My assumption would be that there is a mistake in the condition (given that back when it was implemented it could only be tested with a mock I believe). Since these conditions and the entire expression language is developed by OSF, and we also have no way of knowing what the correct values for the `HasTechnology` check are: can someone from OSF provide us with the correct condition?
Or maybe [~marco.abraham01@vodafone.com]  could you check what the current implementation on DSL side for the corresponding rule is?;;;
column908: 09/Oct/24 12:32 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I got a reply from [~marco.abraham01@vodafone.com], it apparently should be OXGG and not OXC as supplier. I will change it in our rules accordingly.;;;

column918:
13/Oct/24 6:12 PM;lukas.haes1@vodafone.com;Hi [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] 
Die Salesphase ist der Ausbaustatus der Leitung, also ist sie in Betrieb oder wird sie geplant bzw. in naher Zukunft gebaut:
- Regelvermarktung/Standard Sales: GRUEN
- Vorvermarktung/Presales: GELB_GRAU
- Nachverdichtung/Redensification: ORANGE

 

Die Gesamte-Logik wie die VFP interpretiert wird sollte sich meines Wissens nach nicht von DGW oder DTAG unterscheiden. Der unterschied bei OXG ist das eben die Warning Messages angezeigt werden sollen.

 

Sorry it is sunday, I forgot to write in english

@Lukas,
OXG would have some special characters differs from other fiber carriers. Yes, they would have the same product portfolio, but it has few marketing restrictions, for example for those Overbuild cases (in German: Überbaugebiet), for those business details, you guys could ask Niklas Mausberg for details.

column932:
22/Oct/24 3:44 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;The format in which the rules are handed over to OSF is a CSV file.
The CSV file header:
{code:java}
"rule_title";"rule_description";"priority";"is_promo";"is_active";"effective_date";"expiration_date";"rule_type";"show_hint_once";"service_source_expression";"message_title";"message_text";"action";"action_scope";"action_scope_category";"based_on_product";"based_on_category";"channel";"based_on_process_context";"based_on_red_sales_id";"package_type_id" {code}
The rule in question:
{code:java}
"informAboutFtthAvailability";"Display a message to inform the agent that they should talk to the customer about the FTTH availability";"1";"no";"Active";"01.01.00 00:00";;"message_hint";"true";"availability.HasTechnology(null, 1, 'FTTH-L2-BSA', 'GRUEN,GRUEN_GRAU,GELB,ORANGE', '(ACCESS_SUPPLIER;OXGG)')";"WICHTIGER Buchungshinweis - OXG Glasfaserverfügbarkeit";"An dieser Adresse bitte auf FTTH beraten! Für DSL/KIP gilt: Downgrades nur für Wechselgarantie, Upgrades nur auf FTTH erlaubt. Neukunde nur mit max. BB 50 erlaubt.";;;;;"";"Telesales,Retail";"ILSBLU,MIGCOC,MOVE,ACQ";;"CABLE_INTERNET_PHONE" {code}
Which should result for the fields in question:
 * rule_type:
 ** 
message_hint
 * show_hint_once
 ** true
 * message_title:
 ** 
WICHTIGER Buchungshinweis - OXG Glasfaserverfügbarkeit
 * message_text
 ** 
An dieser Adresse bitte auf FTTH beraten! Für DSL/KIP gilt: Downgrades nur für Wechselgarantie, Upgrades nur auf FTTH erlaubt. Neukunde nur mit max. BB 50 erlaubt.
 * communication_variable
 ** *this field does not exist*
 * service_source_expression:
 ** 
availability.HasTechnology(null, 1, 'FTTH-L2-BSA', 'GRUEN,GRUEN_GRAU,GELB,ORANGE', '(ACCESS_SUPPLIER;OXGG)')

Again, since I have access or knowledge about how OSF interprets (or even imports) the rules, it is not possible for me to say why this rule does not work in redensification cases but only in normal cases, which still needs to be analyzed by omnius.
Also note that not a single one of our rules has a field `communication_variable` (the field simply does not exist in the CSV), but all other rules seem to properly work.

*As long as there is no clear instruction _what exactly_ needs to be changed in the above CSV line imported by OSF I will not be able to help on this issue.*;;;

30/Sep/24 7:41 PM;philippe.bretan@vodafone.com;Can the problem be reproduced with a new order?

The order mentioned here was created 2 months ago on August 2nd on test4b/VT4 and not processed until September 27th.

test2b is connected to GIT. That is the reason why the customer cannot be found there.

If the connections from OSF (ACC1-3) to Portals (test1b-4b) were changed between creation and processing of the order, this could also be a reason.

But IMO it is not worth to investigate this further, if the issue cannot be reproduced.;;;
column900:
01/Oct/24 5:39 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  how to handle this defect now? 

I assume the problem is caused by:
 * initial order came from ACC1 when connected to test4b
 * then we moved with ACC1 to test2b before all orders got status updates
 * No ACC environment was connected to test4b until mid of last week
 * after ACC2 was connected to test4b, somehow cable started to send status updates as Test4b was in use again
 * status reached ACC1, but there is now a mismatch because its now connected to test2b and cannot update a customer ID for test4b related to setmarketingpermissions

So its environment mismatch in E2E for older orders;;;
column901: 03/Oct/24 12:31 AM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  [~gopala.tummala@vodafone.com]  should we close this defect as environment issue? see my last comment;;;
column902:
09/Oct/24 12:58 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;email send to cable team 
Dear Cable Team,

Since past releases, we are observing that when we switch the OSF Cable backend Connections (e.g., Test 4b Test2b) somehow after certain period of time Cable env is triggering unexpected SetOrderStatus for the unfinished backend Orders.
E.g.:
•	initial order came from ACC1 when connected to test4b
•	then we moved with ACC1 to test2b before all orders got status updates
•	No ACC environment was connected to test4b until mid of last week
•	after ACC2 was connected to test4b, somehow cable started to send status updates as Test4b was in use again
•	status reached ACC1, but there is now a mismatch because its now connected to test2b and cannot update a customer ID for test4b related to setmarketingpermissions
So, we wanted to ask for some below possible solution from your side to avoid sending this not completed SetOrderCalls towards OSF –as due to this we are generating 100s of SKY tickets.
1.	Whenever we switch from OSF to connect different Cable system—Can we identify the not completed orders from OSF which has reached Cable
2.	If we identify(from point 1) then can we somehow manually complete the order or Stop this SetOrderStatus Process for these orders 
Please let us know if you need some information from our side to identify some old data—like we can provide you the range of OSF orders from the Env and then you can check on your end with unified order id field or something similar reference tracking data.

;;;
column903:
09/Oct/24 12:59 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Feedback from Cable team: 
Hi Rohan,

I don’t think that we have the solution for that right now.
I’ll take this point to discussion in the portals solution and will come back to you.


--So As of now it seems we have an expected behavior from cable where SetOrderStatus call would be triggered unexpectedly for the unfinished orders.
We can conclude and close this defect;;;
column904: 09/Oct/24 1:21 PM;taher.golvala@vodafone.com;Thank you for the confirmation Rohan. We are closing the defect;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | Telesales | DSL telesales new activation orders are completed success even if fast search interface is empty
column41:
While performing sanity we have observed that DSL telesales new activation orders are completed success even if fast search interface is empty

*Step to reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius with Telesales channel

2)Configure DSL Package

3)Submit order

4)Verify OneDMS fast search request

5)Verify OneDMS fast search output

6)Verify OneDMS SaveDocument interface

7)Check order status in OGW and Omnius

*Actual Result:* DSL telesales new activation orders are completed success even if fast search interface is empty

*Expected Result :* Sky ticket should be created if fast search interface is empty

*Test Data:*
Order id/Barcode: 877163/VDE5601873858

ACC1 Telesales Order id : 876649 OGW Order id : 1873098 Barcode: VDE5601873098
Env – IT/ ACC1
column346:
For DSL activation, negative Telesales archiving flow is not working as expected. 
(negative flow: in case document is not archived in OneDMS we receive empty response from OneDMS and we will trigger Fast Search 24 times/ for 2 days. If not successfull after 2 days, Sky ticket is created but that is not sent to OMNIUS (customer) when order got completed success) -> Document is not archived in OneDMS
column591: design gap, now we will add dependency between doc archiving and completed success status
column896:
26/Sep/24 7:05 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;mail chain was started regarding this issue:

 after implement the new US (OS-40463) OGW can get ORDER_COMPLETED from DSL even before doc archiving is finished.

In this case: OS-62529, fast search response is empty, so OGW will wait and try again up to 24 times. Meanwhile DSL is sending us ORDER_COMPLETED status.

So now OGW is sending push Order status to Omnius that order is completed success even though the doc archiving is not yet finished.

Before the implementation of this US (OS-40463) doc_archiving was trigger once ORDER_COMPLETED was receive from DSL, so once doc_archiving was finished only then push order status with completed success was trigger.
[^DSL doc archiving defects.msg];;;

column899:
29/Sep/24 5:25 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,
latest update from Oren Aharoni, the designer:

Oren Aharoni]-  this is design gap and has to be discussed and agree with business,
 * In OS-40463 it was requested to trigger OneDMS call once InProgress FulfillmentStarted received  
 * Later we were requested  to trigger OneDMS after CUSTOMER_CREATED  status provided (attached)
 * Since the time between CUSTOMER_CREATED  to ORDER_COMPLETED  might be short above scenario might happen,

In order to resolve it we can keep dependency between OGW status Completed Success (Order completed)  as prerequisite to trigger OneDMS

This is design change and need VF to agree to new approach.
[^DSL doc archiving defects.msg];;;

column904:
30/Sep/24 7:14 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;after the call this is the solution that were agreed:

OGW will interduce new indicator in the CDM, there we will update once OneDms was sent and was finished.

when we getting completed success from DSL, OGW will check The indicator if OneDms finished.
if yes: OGW will push order status Completed-Success.

if not: flow will be on stand by until we will get response from one dms.
if positive response OGW will push order status Completed-Success.
if negative: OGW will open sky-ticket;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | ACC1 | Close lead logs are not getting generated in OSE servers for closing lead
column41:
Hello,

While performing lead convert scenarios we observed close lead logs are not getting generated in OSE servers for closing lead.

Lead details:

Lead phone number: (0171) 81711112
 
Request_Id__c":"66f168e7b2642"
 
"Lead_Id__c":"LMS-0010434"

Reference stories: OS-52114, OS-50576, OS-50584

*Steps to reproduce:*

Step1: Logging to retail channel
Step2: Enter prospect lead id and clcik on suche button
Step3: search result displayed which are partially masked
Step4: click on search result
Step5: MTAN authentication window should be opens with a phone number(generate MTAN is triggered)
Step6: click on it
Step7: MTAN authentication window should ask for mTAN code sent to phonenumber(when generate MTAN is successfull)
Step8: Enter the code and submit (Validate MTAN is triggered)
Step9: Validate MTAN is successfull
Step10: After succesful mTAN validation prospect lead should be open under product intrest tab in readble formate
Step11: open one Product Interest
Step12: Check under ""Product Interests"" tab in Customer 360 View and Mobile lead should be present and click on convert button from three dots menu
Step13: verify once click on conver button then configurator page should be load with mobile products
Step16: Select the mobile product from configurator and do checkout 
Step17: Verify Omnius should save the Lead Id(""Id"") only if the cart/offer/order contains same package associated with the lead. confirm - the lead was converted for mobile product interest and shopping cart contains the mobile package.  

Verify Omnius should save the Lead Id(""Id"") in database in the following scenario-
1. if agent saves the shopping cart.
2. if agent clicks on ""Send Contract Summary"" button (Telesales).
3. if agent clicks ""Create Documents"" button (Retail).
Step18: Verify Lead Id(""Id"") should further be used to close the Lead after submitting the order in ""Fulfillment"" mode"

Actual Result: Lead closed logs are not getting generated in OSE logs

Actual result: Lead closed logs should get generated in OSE logs as below

Body
{
  "lastUpdateBy__c":"OSF",
  "Current_Sales_Unit_Id__c":"<Sales ID>",
  "Status":"Won", "Close_Date__c":"YYYY-MM-DD",
  "Order_Id__c":"<OMNIUS Order Number>"
}

ACC1 Order id: 877925

ACC2 Order ID: 1124915

*Steps to reproduce:*
 * Login to Omnius Telesales channel.
 * Search for an existing DSL customer.
 * Perform ILS flow.
 * Proceed to checkout.
 * Submit order.
 * Verify InProgress-FulfilmentStarted is received in OGW.
 * Check if Fast Search logs are triggered in OGW.

 
*Expected Result:*

*Actual Result:*

column346:

26/Sep/24 5:33 PM;maheedhar.bekkem@vodafone.com;Hi All,

Please find reference defect [OS-61231] OSF | Wave 9.1 | ACC1/PR | Fast Search logs are not triggered for DSL/FTTH telesales activation/ILS orders - Vodafone Global Jira where this issue was resolved recently after CN_18750 deployment in ACC1 environment.;;;
column897:
26/Sep/24 5:40 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

the issue is the OGW is not triggering the Fast Search
current logic  Fast Search will get trigger when OGW will receive status CUSTOMER_CREATED from DSL.
ACC1: status receive from DSL: ORDER_RECEIVED

ACC2: tatus receive from DSL: ORDER_COMPLETED, ORDER_RECEIVED *5.

acc3: status receive from DSL: ORDER_RECEIVED
 
so for all this cases Fast search will not be trigger;;;

column901:
27/Sep/24 12:43 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi [~alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com] ,

we discuses this yesterday, current behavior if  CUSTOMER_CREATED is not coming so OGW will not trigger doc_archiving.
this was the US.
we created a mail chain to discuses with business regarding this issue. ;;;
column902:
29/Sep/24 5:13 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,
latest update from Oren Aharoni, the designer:

[Oren Aharoni]- This is not defect, it’s  implemented following business requirement, please check attached agreed approach.

It was requested that CUSTOMER_CREATED  status is prerequisite to OneDMS call from OGW.

[^OGW2ONEDMS OS-40463 Z_PRT00145471A.msg];;;
column903: 30/Sep/24 3:54 PM;gokul.vade@vodafone.com;[~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  Will update the correct flow - which need to be implement to resolve this issue ;;;
column904:
30/Sep/24 4:07 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

after the call this is the solution that were agreed:
OGW will call doc_archiving when these 3 conditions are meet:
1. DSL send statuses: CUSTOMER_CREATED or ORDER_RECEIVED

2. inside the sos message will be customer_id

3. a new indicatior will be created inside the CDM, this indicator will check if doc_archiving was trigger.

if true, true, false. then OGW will trigger doc archiving;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | Cable orders are failing at Contract summary for some options
column41:
Cable orders are failing at Contract summary for options like Homespot

Test Data: 

Auftrag ID{*}:{*} 11612937, 11612941, 11621787

*Workaround:*

+KIP:+ 
 * depending on the hardware, mostly HO1:000 (Homespot: minimum contract duration: 0 months) is booked automatically and cannot be deselected – > select the own hardware "[AON] Eigener Kabel-Router vorhanden" under options (this option has also 0 months, but this is ignored, because it's the own hardware of the customer)
 * do not select any other option with the minimum contract duration of 0 months

+!image-2024-09-19-13-16-08-697.png!+

+TV:+
 * for KAD there is no workaround. There are always options booked automatically with a minimum contract duration of 0 months (like DV2:T02, DV2:000, HDC:000) and they cannot be deselected
 * book KAA only (TV Connect)

+KUD:+ 
 * for all GigaTV Appy there is no workaround. The option "ACP:T02" is booked automatically with a minimum contract duration of 0 months
 * for the WLAN Hotspot Flat there is also no workaround as the minimum contract duration is 0 months

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Login to Telesale/Retail channel
 # Perform Cable ACQ 
 # Go to Contract summary page
 # click on Generate Contract

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Omnius is showing all tariff option for mobile tariff change even those products are not compatible with current tariff.
column41:
Hello,

We have observed that Omnius is showing all tariff option for mobile change tariff scenario even those product are not compatible with current tariff

Orders are failing with below error

{*}Error Message{*}:

<ErrorCode>EAI004003</ErrorCode>
<ErrorDescription><![CDATA[An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-ChangeTariff WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI004003, Error_Message: Input tariff option is not plausible with current TO., Error_Type: Functional, Error_Sevirity: E, Error_Information: Input tariff option GM2MOS is not plausible with current TO GM1MOS .,Backend Error Code: 1332] ]]></ErrorDescription>
</DATA>

{*}Order id{*}: 874535

Steps to Reproduce:
Step1: Loging to retail/telesales channel
Step2: search existing mobile customer
Step3: open customer in 360 view and click on packet andern button
Step4: Select any tariff from configurator
Step5: Do checkout
Step6: Submit order

{*}Actual result{*}: Omnius is showing all tariff option for mobile change tariff scenario even those product are not compatible with current tariff

{*}Expected Result{*}: Omnius should show only Compatible tariffs in configurator for change which will not create failure in backend ((KIAS) and order can be processed E2E without failure.

*Step to reproduce:*

2.Perform Availability at FTTH OXG standard/presales/redensification address

3.Verify indicator color for 'Glasfaser Regio-Klasse' 

 

*Test Data:*
Addresses: 
Environment: IT
Standard address -> 90459    Nürnberg    Gibitzenhof    Siemenstr.    14
Presales address -> 35043    Marburg    Cappel    Sommerstr.    1
Redensification address -> 6667    Weißenfels    Weißenfels    Alte Bergstr.    17

*Actual Result :* Omnius shows Red indicator color for 'Glasfaser Regio-Klasse' in availability check information for FTTH OXG standard,presales and redensification address

*Expected Result :* Omnius should display Green indicator color for 'Glasfaser Regio-Klasse' in availability check information for FTTH OXG standard,presales and redensification address

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Getting "404 not found" error message when agent clicks on configurator button in VoiceLog page.
column41:
While Performing Mobile Postpaid New Activation scenario with Online ident, We are getting error message while submitting order which is blocking order submission. When agent close that error message and clicks on Weiter button to change shopping cart, Omnius is showing "404 not found" error message in configurator.
 
Due to this issue, Agent needs to clicks manually on Paket Hinzufugen and then Angebote Mit Vertrag which will activate cart again with same package details.
 
Please find below screenshots:
!image-2024-09-17-11-58-35-981.png|width=511,height=268!

 

!image-2024-09-17-11-50-36-417.png|width=513,height=247!

!image-2024-09-17-11-51-01-419.png|width=528,height=277!

!image-2024-09-17-12-01-16-698.png|width=527,height=276!

!image-2024-09-17-12-02-24-597.png|width=250,height=483!

!image-2024-09-17-12-02-40-500.png|width=499,height=261!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid valid package in shopping cart.
 # Select Online Ident in customer data section.
 # Clicks on submit order button - error received from OGW.
 # Agent close error message.
 # Agent clicks on Configurator button in VoiceLog page.
 # Omnius shows 404 error message when page land in configurator page.
 # Agent needs to select Mobile postpaid package again to activate same cart.

Actual: Getting "404 not found" error message when agent clicks on configurator button in VoiceLog page.

Expected: 
 # Omnius should not show error message and should show active cart when agent clicks on weiter button.
 # If Omnius receive error message when agent clicks on submit order button which leads to deactivate cart, In that case Configurator button should not be clickable.
column346:
When LIG system is down, Agent will get error message on front end for Online Ident. And if he decides to change package data and go back to configurator, getting 404 error message.

No Impact on Online Ident flow when LIG and Backend systems are up and running.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 | INT | ACC1 | Mobile Retail ILS(change Tariff) orders are failed at KIAS-ChangeTariff WS

An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-ChangeTariff WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI000039, Error_Message: Unspecified application error. Please contact system support., Error_Type: Functional, Error_Sevirity: E, Error_Information: Failed to retrieve data from table BILLING_PARAMETERS,Backend Error Code: 9999]

 

*Order Details:*

Omnius Order ID: 873781

OGW Order Id: 1869017

 

{*}Timestamp{*}>2024-09-16T09:12:50.085+02:00

 

<bas:bpName>MFTariff:ChangeTariff</bas:bpName>
<bas:boId>GSM1742300416</bas:boId>
<bas:callingApp>OGW</bas:callingApp>
<bas:initiator>OMNIUS</bas:initiator>

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

1. Login to Retail Channel
2. Search existing customer
3. Perform ILS

5. Proceed to submit order

*Actual Result:* Order are failing with KIAS-ChangeTariff WS error.

*Expected Result:* Orders should not failed with error and status should be OnHold-Pending-POS-HWFulfillment

 

*Note:* This defect is for tracking purpose.

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | GetPickupLocation service is not calling automatically when agent select PDT for Mobile Prepaid.

While performing Mobile Prepaid New Activation flow with PDT, In this scenario, We have observed, GetPickupLocation service is not calling automatically when agent select Lieferung in Vodafone Shop, Paketshop oder Packstation from dropdown.

Same we have checked for Postpaid where it's automatically calling GetPickupLocation service with Customer Address Zipcode (Pincode).

Please find below screenshot for Mobile Prepaid:

!image-2024-09-13-13-03-32-662.png|width=523,height=274!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Valid Mobile Prepaid package with less than 50 Euro Hardware.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Fill Mandatory detail and go to delivery section.
 # Identical to customer address is preselected.
 # Agent select PDT (Lieferung in Vodafone Shop, Paketshop oder Packstation) option.

Actual: GetPickupLocation service is not calling automatically when agent select Lieferung in Vodafone Shop, Paketshop oder Packstation for Mobile Prepaid.

Expected: GetPickupLocation service should call automatically when agent select Lieferung in Vodafone Shop, Paketshop oder Packstation for Mobile Prepaid with Customer Address Zipcode.

Please refer Mobile Postpaid logic.

24/Sep/24 12:47 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;from our BA:

We have identified a new gap in ESIMPush epic, at least for me it looks like a solution gap.

Following are the scenarios :
 # ShiptoStore
 # Telesales/Retail
 # VORAS sending us status [VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT] in StOrderStatus (after H/W is handed out), with OmniusOrderID as OGWSubOrderId .

 

Expectation and issue:

 
 # OGW will identify the OGWOrderID using the OmniusOrderID and then subsequently the Subcriber Information to perform the ESIMPush procedure [ GeteSIMInfo + MaintainEID] .
 # Currently this is failing as in the request we don’t have OrderLineID , hence OGW doesn’t know which OrderLine to pick for subscriber information [it will be trickier if more than one OrerLineID associated with the order] to fetch the Subscriber Info to progress further.

 

Please note: VORAS doesn’t have OrderLineID in talesales scenario.

 

We need to discuss together to close the gap.

column901: 17/Oct/24 5:01 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;No update yet. Still analysis is going on : [~anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com] ;;;
column902:
22/Oct/24 2:39 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;Team Neptune analysed the issue in more detail in [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/CATNEPTUNE-1075]. 

We found that Wizard apparently stores a list of admitted titles in a view called wiz_name_titles, composed of the entries in C_NAME_TITLE_A and 
C_NAME_TITLE_B. Trying the OSF order procedure with various OSF titles that were not present in the Wizard table (from the drop down menu there), we could reproduce the error, e.g., for Dipl.-Ing (BA), Dipl.-Volkswirt and for Dipl.-Ing.oec., while we confirmed for some titles in the table that they are working (see also the examples given above). 

*A solution on OSF side would therefore be to change the GUI as such to only accept values given in Wizard's prod C_NAME_TITLE_A and* 
*C_NAME_TITLE_B tables.* 

Further downstream, we analysed the handling of the field containing the "title" through various stages (VKD Gateway, IBP, AWOP and CVGAPI adapter). CVGAPI is used by OrderSearch, which logs the following: 
{code:java}
Oct 17 13:39:12 vltn865.kabeldeutschland.de z3-test2b-app-wss 
OrderSearchService#2410.2024.09.00.03 62954817 INFO  
getCustomerOrderData  vip_1 REQ(5457d9b99bcefd5de1c14ef4aff0b5e5)  
[ACTIVE] ExecuteThread: '9' for queue: 'weblogic.kernel.Default 
(self-tuning)' de.kabeldeutschland.order.glue.OrderSearchService 
- CustomerOrderDataResult(messages=[], status=SUCCESS, 
customerOrderData=CustomerOrderData(processing=Processing(webOrderId=6137694, 
orderSubType=NEU, unifiedOrderId=1893590, orderStatus=OPEN, 
customerId=null, customerIdUme=null, creationDate=2024-10-17T11:10:32.000Z, 
target=KDG, region=R09, comment=null, source=ECC, sourceDetail=OFT, 
dealer=VA177001, salesId=99834, neutralSalesAgent=null, 
control=--- --- --- --- KUD,-- -- -- -- --, AWOP_ERROR , 
campagne=MGM, cancellationReason=null, 
postProcessing=PostProcessing(counter=1, lastAgent=qaappsupport, 
lastDate=null, nextDate=null, reason=null), opMessages=[OpMessage(nr=1, 
orderId=6137694, retry=1, source=cvgapi_adapter, scope=CCB_IF69, 
key=webcsc.ccbapi.services.cvgapi.OpenCnWoForCustomerOnlyCmd.311008, 
severity=E, subOrderId=NEU, text=311008: 
Invalid title post code : Dipl.-Finanzwirt Enter a valid title in ... {code}
 

We see that the order retrieval as such was successful, but that the order is corrupted. Even before, the AWOP_ERROR flag got added; this happens if AWOP finds error messages logged  by AWOP if there was an error beforehand by analysing it with the hasErrors() method.

We are therefore quite sure that the error happens in the processing between OSF and AWOP, i.e., probably in VKDGateway and IBP. Unfortunaltely, we could not find any filtering mechanism or validation thatid responsible for throwing the error. From VKD side, adding the UME fields might help, but it is hard to say if this really helps because of the high compplexity of what happens in between. Probably, the easiest would be the solution suggested above: Forbid the OSF GUI users to choose values not supported by the Wizard tables C_NAME_TITLE_A and C_NAME_TITLE_B by deleting these values from the frontend.

*This is only about VKD customers. The Wizard has got nothing to do with UME/ VF West customers* ;;;
column903:
22/Oct/24 8:44 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com]  maybe you can check with OSF design team if we need OSF CR for change of the behavior as proposed by Cable

Probably, the easiest would be the solution suggested above: Forbid the OSF GUI users to choose values not supported by the Wizard tables C_NAME_TITLE_A and C_NAME_TITLE_B by deleting these values from the frontend.;;;

column1: CR Required | OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Omnius is showing "Contract summary will be sent as a letter" message when agent retrieved saved Mobile Prepaid Offer.
column41:
While performing Mobile Prepaid Saved offer, we have observed, Omnius is showing Contract summary will be sent a letter message when agent retrieved saved Mobile Prepaid Offer.

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2024-09-12-20-31-35-575.png|width=328,height=282!

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
2. Create Mobile Prepaid package.
3. Proceed to checkout.
4. Save offer using Sent to BO button.
5. Retrieve saved offer using offer manager (Agent is having *CS_VIA_LETTER* permission).
6. Clicks on edit offer and verify Die Vertragszusammenfassung wird als Brief versendet message.

Actual: Omnius is showing Contract summary will be sent a letter message when agent retrieved saved Mobile Prepaid Offer.

Expected: Omnius should not show this message for Mobile Prepaid as Contract Summary is not required (not yet implemented).

Reference stories: OS-4172 OMNIUS CHCK - As an agent in Telesales, I want to move to Voicelog in case contractual documents are not needed for print and signature, so that I can send the order to fulfillment. OS-4172 - Vodafone Global Jira

OS-21136 Omnius _CHCK: As an agent, I want to see overview summary at the end of the checkout in case customer has opted for CS via letter OS-21136 - Vodafone Global Jira

------------------

so - the situation is as follows:

1) For use case save offer which is described in this ticket, we receive "ContractSummaryCreationInd = 'False'" Response from OGW in GenerateContract -> CORRECT

2) The customer is not getting CS document - not via email and not via letter for this use case -> CORRECT 

3) For some reason, Omnius shows *Die Vertragszusammenfassung wird als Brief versendet* in Voice Log, +although it does not make any sense at all+ based on point 1 & 2 -> *{color:#de350b}WRONG{color}*

But as per TechM its expected and requested functionality (we do not have any user story request for this dedicated use case).
column346: For Mob Prepaid saved offer unexpected message related to CS is shown on Voicelog page. For Mob Prepaid no CS is expected and its also no created, therefore only a display error
column591: No change required.

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Different account holder section is deselected when agent change payment option in Hardware payment section.
column41:
While performing Mobile SOHO Business New Activation scenario in Telesales channel, We have observed that, Different account holder section is deselected when agent select ByInvoice option in Hardware payment section. In case agent again select Different account holder section, Contact person name is erase from input field.

Please find below screenshots:

!image-2024-09-12-14-14-50-871.png|width=530,height=278!

!image-2024-09-12-14-15-32-103.png|width=530,height=278!

!image-2024-09-12-14-15-58-382.png|width=529,height=277!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create valid Mobile SOHO Business with or without skeleton contract.
 # Proceed to checkout and verify payment (Zahlungsoptionen) section.
 # Select Direct Debit (Per Bankeinzug) option in Monthly payment (Monatliche Zahlungsdaten) section.
 # Select Account holder is a different person (Abweichender Kontoinhaber) section and fill mandatory details.
 # Select ByInvoice (Per Rechnung) payment option in Hardware payment (Zahlungsart für Ihre Lieferung) section.
 # Account holder is a different person (Abweichender Kontoinhaber) section is deselected and Omnius select Customer is account holder (Kunde ist Kontoinhaber) section.
 # When agent again select Account holder is a different person (Abweichender Kontoinhaber), Contact person name is erase from input field.

Actual: Different account holder section is deselected when agent select ByInvoice option in Hardware payment section.

Expected:
 # Different account holder section should not be deselected when agent select ByInvoice option in Hardware payment section or change payment method in Hardware payment section.
 # If current behavior is expected, then Contact person name should not be erase from input field.

Reference story: [OS-9067] Omnius CHCK As an agent, I want to be able to capture company name as bank account owner related to Mobile SOHO Business customer, so that correct account owner is provided [OS-9067] - Vodafone Global Jira
column346: Agent needs to select different account holder option again after changing hardware payment method and contact person details has to enter again.

I uploaded a new cable pcat to the pcat-int with support for a proxy parameter as discussed today in the call.

The pcat version is V2410_2024_09_00_079_D01.

[@Sandeep Kumar Pradhan|mailto:SP00123672@Techmahindra.com]/[@Akhilesh Sawarkar|mailto:Akhilesh.Sawarkar@TechMahindra.com] please provide an implementation {_}{{_}}asap{{_}}{_}.
The change is simply in the constructor of the `RemoteServiceParameters` class which now takes an additional optional parameter `proxy`:
> public function __construct(string $url, string $username, string $password, string $productSetupVersion, string $proxy = "")

The proxy can be provided in the form of “<some host/ip>:<some port>” for example.

[@Sandeep Kumar Pradhan|mailto:SP00123672@Techmahindra.com] regarding your comment: “Also an open point is that with this proxy setting of plugin version we need to check if that will work on OSE web server as well where it is working fine at the moment without proxy”. That is correct, however the correct proxy value {_}{{_}}must{{_}}{_} be provided by Omnius, there is no way of guessing the correct value for the cable rules plugin. Whether or not Omnius needs a separate configuration for this I honestly do not really care, the option to pass the value into the plugin exists and Omnius now has to provide the correct values.;;;

2) configure any package/ ILS

3) submit order

4) process the order and check the status in OGW and omnius order manager

 

Expected Result:

we should get the proper logs in OGW and proper pushorderstatus should get triggered towards omnius

column905:
16/Sep/24 1:30 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback after manual configuration change on Friday

In the fix We added configuration to WF EG: JMS_AUXILIARY_KAFKA_STATUS_EG.

We added group.id to the provider url property.

The problem that we added it incorrectly, so after deployment the group id was in the general properties of the EG and not inside the provider url.

For TID team:

If this happened we don’t need to do any restart, we can change this properties inside JESI admin.
 # Stop the EG JMS_AUXILIARY_KAFKA_STATUS_EG in WF under this path: vfde
 # Click on update EG and to add to the end of provider URL this: &group.id=JMS_AUXILIARY_KAFKA_STATUS_EG_ACC1
 # Start the EG

{color:#de350b}*-> so now workaround is in place again and issue is fixed, but we still need to get permanent fix*{color} ;;;

column897:
06/Sep/24 3:50 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I reproduced this issue on one of our cloud sandboxes using the same OSE and PCAT version as on the ACC1.
The attached cable-rules-log ([^cable_rules_artifact1105120.log)] shows some interesting behaviour that leads me to believe that this is an OSF issue, or that at least OSF will have to analyse why the products are deselected.

Log analysis:
 * Searching through the logs for CGTP006 (the tariff that was selected) gives the following results:
 ** CGTP006 is not selected in the beginning ("|CGTP006|false|true|false|true|")
 ** CGTP006 is selected in the input for a few iteration ("|CGTP006|true|true|false|true|")
 ** CGTP006 is selected in the output for the last iteration where it was selected in the input ("ProductId: CGTP006, visible: false, selected:  true")
 ** CGTP006 is not selected in the next input ("|CGTP006|false|false|false|true|")
 * -> OSF deselects the main tariff CGTP006

From the cable configuration that could have this effect I do not see any configuration that should have this effect in this scenario (no radio groups, no relation excludes).

I believe it to be highly likely that the root cause for this bug is the same as for https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-61427;;;

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Omnius allows to proceed with Direct debit hardware payment option even if agent provided foreign IBAN in monthly payment.
column41:
While performing Mobile Postpaid New Activation with Mobile prepaid scenario with Carrie Ident and Foreign IBAN for monthly payment, In this scenario, We have observed that Omnius allows to proceed with Direct debit hardware payment option even if agent provided foreign IBAN in monthly payment section.

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2024-09-05-15-55-07-376.png|width=398,height=463!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Prepaid package in shopping cart.
 # Add New Mobile postpaid package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout and select carrier ident in checkout.
 # Add/Select Mandatory data in Customer data, new connection section.
 # Enter Foreign IBAN in monthly payment setion.
 # Verify Hardware payment options in payment section.

Actual: Omnius allows to proceed with Direct debit hardware payment option even if agent provided foreign IBAN in monthly payment.

Expected:  Omnius should not allow to proceed with Direct debit hardware payment option if agent provided foreign IBAN in monthly payment and hardware payment should be done via ByInvoice payment option.

Reference story: [OS-35] CHCK As an agent I should be forced to capture the payment method "auf Rechnung" for one time charges (for mobile hardware) - Vodafone Global Jira

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Pay in Store (Zahlung im Shop) payment option missing in hardware payment section for Vodafone store delivery option.
column41:
Pay in Store (Zahlung im Shop) payment option missing in hardware payment section for Vodafone store delivery option in case of Mobile Postpaid with Prepaid New acquisition. 

Please find below screenshots:

Pay in Store (Zahlung im Shop) payment option missing in Hardware payment section:

!image-2024-09-05-14-50-46-920.png|width=353,height=361!

Pay in Store (Zahlung im Shop) payment option present in Hardware payment section:

!image-2024-09-05-14-56-51-479.png|width=353,height=367!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Prepaid package in shopping cart.
 # Add New Mobile postpaid package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout and select store ident in checkout.
 # Add/Select Mandatory data in Customer data, new connection section.
 # Select PDT - Vodafone store option in delivery section for Mobile Postpaid.
 # Verify Hardware payment options in payment section (Zahlungsart für Ihre Lieferung).

Actual: Pay in Store (Zahlung im Shop) payment option missing in hardware payment section for Vodafone store delivery option in case of Mobile Postpaid with Prepaid New acquisition. 

Expected: Pay in Store (Zahlung im Shop) payment option only shown as preselected in hardware payment section for Vodafone store delivery option in case of Mobile Postpaid with Prepaid New acquisition. 

If Mobile Prepaid order contains Mobile Postpaid New Package with Vodafone store ident method & delivery option, Omnius should priorities Mobile Postpaid and should show Vodafone store delivery applicable payment option for Hardware.

Reference story: [OAF-76] Ommius OSE: As an Agent, i want to capture new payment method for Hardware Package . So that ship2store delivery will process in legacy system. - Vodafone Global Jira
column346:
Payment Method “Pay in Store” is mandatory for this shipping option. This has financial reasons in SAP (Invoicing and issue of the product needs to be closer on a timely manner).

(If order contains only postpaid, No issue in payment options).

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | By Invoice payment option missing in hardware payment section for Mobile Postpaid with Prepaid New acquisition.
column41:
By Invoice payment option missing in payment section for Mobile Postpaid with Prepaid New acquisition. 

In case of Mobile Postpaid is part of order with Prepaid - Postpaid payment option must be shown in payment section.

Please find below screenshots:

By Invoice (Per Rechnung) payment option missing in payment section:

!image-2024-09-05-14-07-07-392.png|width=366,height=371!

By Invoice (Per Rechnung) payment option is present for Mobile Postpaid:

!image-2024-09-05-14-11-35-710.png|width=374,height=429!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Prepaid package in shopping cart.
 # Add New Mobile postpaid package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Add/Select Mandatory data in Customer data, new connection & delivery section.
 # Verify Hardware payment options in payment section (Zahlungsart für Ihre Lieferung).

Actual: By Invoice payment option missing in hardware payment section for Mobile Postpaid with Prepaid New acquisition.

Expected: By Invoice option must be shown in hardware payment section for Mobile Postpaid & Prepaid New Activation order (single order with prepaid & postpaid stack).

If Mobile Prepaid order contains Mobile Postpaid New Package, Omnius should priorities Mobile Postpaid and should show same payment method which is shown for single mobile postpaid package.
column346:

(If order contains only postpaid, No issue in payment options).
