column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Omnius allows to capture new details in checkout section for second delivery use case.
column41:
We have observed that, Omnius allows to capture new details in checkout section even if existing details are valid for second delivery use case.

Please find below screenshots and Issues:

1. Omnius allows to Capture New Porting details:

!image-2024-09-03-16-49-25-535.png|width=356,height=375!

!image-2024-09-03-16-50-11-313.png|width=357,height=369!

2. Omnius allows to Capture New Delivery details:

!image-2024-09-03-17-04-07-807.png|width=526,height=276!

!image-2024-09-03-17-25-48-841.png|width=324,height=259!

2. Omnius allows to Capture New Payment address:

!image-2024-09-03-17-05-49-313.png|width=524,height=275!

!image-2024-09-03-17-26-38-976.png|width=403,height=186!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Agent logged in Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Agent loaded existing Customer which is eligible for second delivery.
 # Agent clicks on SECOND DELIVERY (Zweitversand) button and created a valid shopping cart
 # Agent reached to checkout page on Customer data section.
 # Verify Porting section, delivery section and payment section in checkout.

Expected: 
 # Porting: Section should be in read only mode when Porting was not captured in Original Order/package. means Agent can't captured new porting data.
 # Delivery & Billing Address: If customer is having correct & valid delivery & Biling Address - 
 ## Delivery method should prefilled and read only mode from Original Order/Package.And no change of delivery method is allowed. 
 ##  Agent should see in Payment section in readonly mode and for all section data should be prefillef from Customer installed base.

Reference stories:

OAF-102 OMNIUS : CHCK As an Agent, i wanted to prefill porting details from Original Order when porting was captured,so that second delivery package should consider as Original package/Order with Porting details. - Vodafone Global Jira

OAF-104 OMNIUS : CHCK As an Agent, i wanted to prefill same Delivery method from Original Order as it was captured,so that second delivery package should consider as Original package/Order with Delivery details. - Vodafone Global Jira

OAF-105 OMNIUS : CHCK As an Agent, i wanted to prefill Payment details from Customer installed base info ,so that second delivery package should consider exisitng installed base payment method. - Vodafone Global Jira

[OAF-189] OMNIUS : CHCK As an Agent, i wanted Delivery method (home address) prefilled and editable for second delivery package from Original order. So that it will possible to changed Delivery method and edit delivery details. - Vodafone Global Jira

column909:
25/Sep/24 6:12 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
 
Hi [~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com] 

Based on the further analysis it is identified that the Original is created by the Prospect/New customer (i.e, No address or IBAN on IB) during checkout we are collecting all the information like IBAN address via new IBAN and new address fields.

But when we perform second delivery for such order, we will not have any existing information on customer IB and still system allows customer to capture the address details and show the same address or payment methods which are originally captured during the first order.

This is expected behavior in the above new customer case.

If we perform second delivery for existing customer orders, then it will be in reuse mode with disabled fields for payment and the billing address by picking details from InstallBase.

So, we will deliver the fix only for the first case i.e
 # Porting: Section should be in read only mode when Porting was not captured in Original Order/package. means Agent can't captured new porting data.

Thanks;;;

 # Login to Telesales/Retail channel

column591: HF26 is finally deployed now too and version of SOC XSD is back to 04.05
column896:
30/Aug/24 3:42 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;comments from TEMS team:-
We received this  EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd  file  in  OCA.000160779 /OC.000160773  (OPM_430.01.24.00)  and this is installed in PR Env as a part of OCA.


Let me clarify the issue here, Currently IT Env is with BSS44 and IT OPM is currently running with Soc version EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd.
In same way as per last OPM deployment [OCA.000160779 /OC.000160773  (OPM_430.01.24.00) ] on PR Env, the similar Soc version has been deployed EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd.

Now both IT and PR OPM is using the same soc version EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd, But from Soc side only IT Env having the latest version 0406.
PR Soc is still running on version 0405, So since the last deployment on PR OPM the incoming requests are using the latest version 0406 but from Soc side its still has the lower version.

That’s the reason the test cases are stuck at Oms-Warte-Antwort step in PR OPM.
To resolve this issue either PR OPM should be downgraded to version EPSM-SOC-0405.xsd or PR Soc version should be upgraded to 0406.
;;;

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Multiple search results window shown in Payment section for Mobile SOHO Business even if entered address is correct.
column41:
While performing Mobile Postpaid SOHO Business New Activation in Telesales channel with Different account holder option, in this scenario, we are getting Multiple search results window in Payment section even if entered address is correct and validated. In case agent close "Mehrere Suchergebnisse" window and select any option in payment section which will lead to appear window again.

Please find below screenshot & attached document.

!image-2024-08-27-17-46-54-362.png|width=507,height=266!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile SOHO Business package.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Validate IBAN in Monthly payment section.
 # Select Different account holder and Enter Address.
 # Address verification successfully done.
 # Select ByInvoice option for Hardware payment.
 # Observed issue - Multiple search result window appears.
 # Close window and select any option in payment section which will lead to appear window again.

Actual: Multiple search results window shown in Payment section for Mobile SOHO Business even if entered address is correct.

Expected: Multiple search results window should not appear in Payment section for Mobile SOHO Business if entered address is correct and already validated in Omnius.

Note: Even after selecting address from appearing screen, Address is selected & added in different account holder section but when agent select ByInvoice option in HW payment section, screen again appear. so, In each & every condition "Mehrere Suchergebnisse" screen appears.
column346: Address Result screen appears which needs to close every time when it's again appears in payment section & without closing that screen agent cannot continue sales flow.

Well in short note, this is not a defect.

This is agreed behaviour in *CR659* , when in Omnius UI Agent captured an address the later it validate via service call (ValdiateAddress) And in case when service result multiple address in response for captured address then Omnius shows modal with list of all address received from response to make selection by Agent.

If modal appears multiple place this is because of address is validate via service on multiple palaces during checkout and service result multiple address in response.

 

Hope this is helpful;;;

column1: OSF | Wave9.1 | ACC1 | Identification method is changing to SOHO when agent refresh Omnius session on customer data page.
column41:
While performing Mobile New Activation postpaid test scenario in Telesales channel, We have observed that Identification method is changing to SOHO when agent refresh Omnius session on customer data page.

This issue is observed for every identification method, i.e. agent saved customer data using Online Ident, Store Ident, DHL Ident, Carrier Ident these identification method and agent refresh Omnius page after saving customer data section and again agent continuing flow with same identification method and observed after saving customer data, Omnius is showing SOHO identification method.

Create Valid Mobile Postpaid package with Hardware and Tariff:

!image-2024-08-26-18-22-56-122.png|width=504,height=265!

Carrier Ident selected:

!image-2024-08-26-18-23-51-881.png|width=504,height=265!

!image-2024-08-26-18-24-45-985.png|width=501,height=263!

!image-2024-08-26-18-31-37-175.png|width=501,height=263!

!image-2024-08-26-18-32-19-672.png|width=501,height=263!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid package.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Select Online Ident, Store Ident, DHL Ident, Carrier Ident.
 # Save Customer data.
 # Refresh Omnius session.
 # Again, clicks on Weiter button.
 # Omnius shows SOHO identification method when agent saved customer data section.

Actual: Identification method is changing to SOHO when agent refresh Omnius session on customer data page.

Expected: Identification method should not change and should show same identification method which agent has selected when agent refresh Omnius session on customer data page.
column346: Incorrect Identification method shown in saved customer data which will create confusion to agent/customer (GUI issue, No impact on functional flow).
column591:
This is special scenario in which we have multiple radio button with different name, so in this case OSE was accepting all active radio button. So need to handle specially this case while checking selected/saved value through Jquery.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | Regression | DSL offers created with July PCAT are automatically changed with August PCAT Release
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (PR)

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test offer: 

CS ID: 11721936; OSF Order ID: 1104477 (created on 8th of August, {*}valid for 8 days{*})

 

*+Please note:+* 
 * when creating a new offer with the DSL PCAT August Release (ACC2) and opening the offer on the same environment, the bug does not appear, e. g.:

          1. CS ID: 11730890; OSF Order ID: 1105207 (created on 9th of August)

          2. CS ID: 11747135 (created on 12th of August)
 * when creating a new offer with the DSL PCAT July Release (ACC1) and opening the offer on the same environment, the bug does not appear, e. g.:

          1. CS ID: 11748105; OSF Order ID: 862241 (created on 12th of August)

 

{+}Actual result{+}: DSL offers created with July PCAT are automatically changed with August PCAT Release

 

+Expected result:+ DSL offers created with July PCAT should not be automatically changed with PCAT August Release, because the offers on production should be valid for 14 days

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * create a DSL offer in July Release (DSL 250, DSL 50, DSL 100)
 * e. g.: DSL 50 +c"[GS_DSL_9x30E[br]] 9 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis" + "[GS_DSL_100E[br]] 100 Euro Startguthaben" + "[GS_YOUNG_24x5E[br]] Kunde ist unter 28 Jahre alt (GigaZuhause Young)" ({*}has to be addd manually{*})  - CS ID: 11721936; OSF Order ID: 1104477 (created on 8th of August, {*}valid for 8 days{*})

*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------*

*Please note:* 
 * "[GS_DSL_9x30E[br]] 9 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis" is not valid anymore with the DSL PCAT August Release, instead of the for new activation orders with DSL 50 the promo "[GS_DSL_12x30E[br]] 12 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis" is booked
 * "GS_DSL_100E[br]] 100 Euro Startguthaben" is not valid in DSL PCAT August Release and it should be not booked at all
 * "[GS_YOUNG_24x5E[br]] Kunde ist unter 28 Jahre alt (GigaZuhause Young)" is not bookable in DSL PCAT August Release

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * make sure that the DSL Augst PCAT Release is deployed on ACC2
 * search for the offer (CS ID): 11721936 
 * select the prospect customer data
 * click on the 3 dots menue and select "Bearbeiten"

– > Checkout is loaded – > *OK*
 * continue with the order until the Order Overview

– >  wrong data is displayed --> *NOT OK*
 # "[GS_DSL_12x30E[br]] 12 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den" ** is booked instead of "[GS_DSL_9x30E[br]] 9 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis"
 # "[LS_DSLBASECHARGE_2E[br]EOL] Basispreisanteil 2 EUR (monatlich)" is booked instead of "[LS_DSL_SURCHARGE_5E[br]EOL] Basispreisanteil 5 EUR (monatlich)"
 # "[GS_WoWi_5E[br]EOL] Sonder-Rabatt 5 Euro" is booked
 # "[LS_Regio-Zuschlag_5E[br]EOL] Regio-Zuschlag" is booked
 # "[GS_YOUNG_24x5E[br]] Kunde ist unter 28 Jahre alt (GigaZuhause Young)" is missing
 # "[LS_YOUNG_9x5E[br]] Ausgleich Gutschrift Young 1.-9. Monat" is missing

!image-2024-08-12-18-23-45-550.png!

Original CS (see attached in "Email"):

!image-2024-08-12-18-28-04-199.png!

column1: OSF|W9.1|ACC1 |Assisted Sanity| v9.20.0-BB8 | Getting Error message on order Overview and customer detail page for solstice order
column41:
Error Message - Der Auftrag kann wegen eines technischen Fehlers nicht abgeschickt werden. Bitte versuche es später erneut. (Correlation-ID: lr0j2pa4v7dqqubje9i743ql7i)

The order cannot be sent due to a technical error. Please try again later. (Correlation ID: lr0j2pa4v7dqqubje9i743ql7i)

Steps to reproduce 
 # Login to Telesales
 # Perform Check serviceability 
 # select solstice product and tariff
 # Move to zum checkout and click on zum checkout button 
 # fill all the required details on customer details 
!image-2024-08-12-18-41-37-369.png!

          6. Proceed till offer overview page 

Actual Result   if response code other than 200, it will consider as failure and it will display technical error msg, and block the agent to continue 

!image-2024-08-12-18-45-09-491.png!

!image-2024-08-12-18-46-54-860.png!

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2/PR | DSL /FTTH Phase 2 order is going to fulfillment started status after completed success again
column41:
While performing below scenario, we have observed that DSL /FTTH order is going to fulfillment started status after completed success again

*Observations:*

There is only 1 second difference between ORDER_POSITION_COMPLETE(1286) and ORDER_COMPLETED(1290) *if we are processing order next day*

And {*}OGW is processing ORDER_COMPLETED earlier than ORDER_POSITION_COMPLETE{*}, and hence order goes to fullfillment started status again

21/Jul/24 1:26 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

i saw what Marco wrote. but it is the issue.

OGW is picking the status at the same time

!image-2024-07-21-10-52-51-438.png!

these 2 statuses working at the same time. 

in our case the completed success process is finishing 1 second before so you are seeing the push order status completed success first.

InProgress-FulfillmentStarted is finishing 1 second after the completed success, so you will see push order status  InProgress-FulfillmentStarted last.

 

 

!image-2024-07-21-10-56-55-623.png!;;;
column899:
22/Jul/24 7:40 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  maybe you can detail the scenario bit more in context of CR553 (not the enhancement, but the solution which is already in place)

For every transaction considered for handling, OGW will search for the transactions by OrderID in the subscribe table.
 * If no other entries found, process the current transaction.
 * If +legacy+ timestamp (or its analogue – ts+sequence, like in KIAS) is populated:
 * If younger (by {+}*legacy timestamp*{+}) +processed+ entries found, the order of transactions was violated. SKY ticket should be opened, and the flow suspended until resolution.
 * Else if older (by {+}*legacy timestamp*{+}) +unprocessed+ entries found, pick the earliest unprocessed entry and handle it.

what is our expectation now in the context of this ticket.
The timestamp of the status is not exactly the same, but in between there are just miliseconds. 
So this is not covered by CR553 introducted in wave 7.x?;;;
column900:
22/Jul/24 7:54 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;the issue is that OGW will pick the correct sos from the db, but it will not stop there.

it will not wait until the entire process of InProgress-FulfillmentStarted is finished. 

so in that case InProgress-FulfillmentStarted has an advantage of a few miliseconds, but seems the flow of InProgress-FulfillmentStarted is a bit slower then completed-success.

so what happened is that completed-success is finishing a few miliseconds before and sending push order status.

after a few miliseconds inProgress-FulfillmentStarted is finishing and also send push order status, and because its the last one its reflecting in frontEnd;;;

column896:
09/Jul/24 5:15 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;Analysis on PCAT side was done by [~tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com] :

Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

10/Jul/24 5:09 PM;gauri.bhagat@vodafone.com;Below are some of the findings after the call with Waseem,

It has impact ONLY IF all three switches are Yes If anyone of them is No then there is no impact. We have checked in PROD all three switches are set to 'No' So ACC team cannot decide for PROD, decision has to take by Fusion C team if they want Switches Yes. ;;;
column900:
10/Jul/24 6:57 PM;sandeepkumar.pradhan@vodafone.com;Hi All,

{*}Why issue Occurred{*}: Since all the 3 field for CustomerDataHUB Solution1 Settings and CustomerDataHUB Settings  such as

CustomerDataHUB Solution1 Settings 
1)Central Search ES Interfaces Enabled

CustomerDataHUB Settings
1)Legacy search and MRT Enabled
2)Enable CDH Interface
are set to "Yes" which breaks the API flow in current OSE build  which is not the case in ACC1 or PROD
in both these environment at least one of the them or all are set as "NO" where both customer search and Installed base working fine (for PRODUCTION all filed set as NO)


{*}Action plan{*}: we need to work with Vodafone design team to understand on what criteria these all filed need to switch on (Set as yes) after that or parallelly we need look from OSE prospective how we can handle these API irrespective of setting (all 3 set to YES or all 3 set to NO(working condition) or partial set of YES and NO (working condition))
 

Also PROD and ACC2 are almost equal we should ensure that ACC2 setting always same that of PROD else conf change leads to issue like this , Do understand that tACC2 setting can be change too for testing but it has to be known to an extent;;;
column901:
11/Jul/24 12:02 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~sandeepkumar.pradhan@vodafone.com]  the settings on ACC and in PROD will never be exactly same, as we are always testing future topics in ACC which might not be live yet.
However, for these Fusion C switches we had topics in scope for different releases, so the functionality itself is live since a long time but with a technical go live.

1)[OS-8975] SOL0 - Search & display customer with product(s) mastered in solstice - Vodafone Global Jira -> implemented with Wave 7.0, tested with Wave 7.1  

2) [OS-11283] SOL1SE32 - Extending the OSF Search for Solstice Customers - Vodafone Global Jira -> initially implemented with Wave 7.2, because of needed enhancement tested again with Wave 9.0 

We are not having any new functionality, the switches are there since years. 
To retest your TechM fix for OS-56961 of course all switches had to be YES and in release Wave 9.0 they have been on YES in general most of the time, as OS-11283 was part of Wave 9.0 and tested by Fusion C team.

As ACC1 was used for Wave 8.2 of course ACC1 was different, as there only OS-8975 was live already (therefore only one switch was enabled) 

And as its technically live, Fusion C team can decide at any time to switch it ON in production. Its like any other technical go live, where functionaly is enabled in ACC but not yet in production.;;;

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version
column41:
*Description:* For UM Scenario we observed issue as BEW version is not updating in Backend and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version.

 

*Test Data:*

281507501

*documentID:* 10832608

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Retail channel as FI/PA agent.
Search existing *UM* customer with ADV and DEV version less than 4.
Retrieve the customer and click on BEW Bearbeiten button.
Verify BEW banner notification.
Select BEW ERFASSEN.
Select checkbox for ADV/DEV.
Click on "Dokument erstellen"(Create document) button
Document will be generated.
After that search the customer again.
select BEW Bearbeiten button.
BEW Erfassen button should not available/disable.

 

*Actual Result:* BEW version is not updating in Backend and BEW Erfassen is enable, even after update the version.

*Expected Result:* BEW version should be update in Backend and BEW Erfassen button should be disable after updating the version.

 

*Reference Defect:*

[OS-56676]

column904:
11/Jul/24 7:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  based on the latest calls e have the following findings for Retail BEW and unitymedia in general

1) New customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

2) Existing customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

3) Existing customer, Retail, BEW only ->{color:#de350b} *Backend receives and stores BEW correctly? Please confirm this*
{color:#172b4d}What is wrong in all cases -> Frontend OSF is not able to retrieve the right BEW settings. So if BEW was updated in UNitymedia backend, Frontend is not reflecting this. It still looks like no BEW is set{color} ** 
{color:#172b4d}We will also compare the same for VKD, how Retrievecustomerinfo Mode 3 related to BEW permissions is looking like{color}{color};;;
column906:
12/Jul/24 7:08 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  the ticket itself is only for Unitymedia, so for VKD its not a problem and no ticket reported.

We still need to document here, if the Existing customer, Retail, BEW only for Unitymedia is reaching the backend as ticket says 

_*{color:#de350b}BEW version is not updating in Unity Backend{color}* and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version._

 

At the moment we assume, BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but we cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version 
Unitymedia is handling permissions with Version 2, OGW expecting Version  4 and for retrieval of existing permissions we get Version 0.

Needs to be checked with responsible person from MinervaAdapter (VKD side);;;
column907: 17/Jul/24 2:34 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;No progress yet as we did not identify the responsible person who can help with Minerva Adapter VKD ;;;
column908:
18/Jul/24 9:28 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;I have enclosed the latest discussion.
As per latest analysis this problem is related to the way back from Unitymedia via Minerva Adapter VKD to OGW

{color:#de350b}*OK:*{color} OGW version 4 -> Minerva Adapter maps Version 4 from the VKD request into Version 2 for the request to UME/VFW -> UME/VFW is storing Version 2 correctly in Mood and showing right entries in RNS for the customer 

{color:#00875a}*Not OK*{color}: Now when we open the customer who has given BEW again in OSF, we expect that the stored BEW is taken and we are not asked to capture BEW again. Problem: For this get_permission Call we are receiving version 0 for the mentioned scenarios and we cannot map this version to our valid Version 4 (not OK)

{+}*Gap*{+}: We need a Mapping: UME/VFW is sending back Version 2 to Minerva Adapter-> Minerva Adapter maps Version 2 to Version 4 if getpermission request is coming from OGW

 

I have shared the feedback also with Jörg Trierweiler, Thomas Schneider, Andreas Baldermann and few more people to verify.
This is a general topic and not specifically related to BEW only Retail Epic
Waiting for feedback about possible next steps;;;

currently while performing ILS customer having any existing insurance can also see the different options to select from configurator.

[~gokul.vade@vodafone.com]  [~ajay.bhavar@vodafone.com]

this ACC tracking Bug can now be retestet on ACC1 with the *+2nd scenario+* ->{+}{+}no Insurance option should be visible(see description below)

Existing customers on ACC1 they can be used for the retest:
|Customer ID|Subscriber Number|Tariff Option|SOC|
|104724208|GSM1738852612|GM1LH30 |24HATAV17|
|110016580|GSM1726591197|GM1MH40 |24HATAV17|
|107241788|GSM1792332596|GM1LH40 |24HATAV17|
|104058520|GSM1727077848|SMART3XXL|24HATAV17|

 

*(*)New Change(*)*

*+1st scenario:+*

SOC “sales expired” -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is no longer offered + Vodafone device, which was purchased no longer than 120 days ago

Expected result: Customer can book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = true)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase <120 days) & tariff + legacy(or Cover or Cover Plus) SOC “sales expired” = true

 

*+2nd scenario:+*

SOC “sales expired”, but device too old -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is no longer offered, + Vodafone device, which was purchased more than 120 days ago

Expected result: User cannot book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = true)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase >120 days) & tariff + Legacy/Cover/CoverPlus SOC “sales expired” = true

 

*+3rd scenario:+*

SOC NOT sales expired -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is still offered + Vodafone device, which was purchased no longer than 120 days ago

Expected result: User cannot book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = false)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase <120 days) & tariff + legacy/Cover/CoverPlus SOC “sales expired” = false

 

*+4th scenario:+*

SOC NOT sales expired, but device too old -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is still offered + Vodafone device, which was purchased more than 120 days ago.

Expected result: User cannot book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = false)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase >120 days) & tariff + legacy/Cover/CoverPlus SOC “sales expired” = false

column1: OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | Omnius allows to select new identification method in Kundenidentifikation section for second delivery use case.
column41:
While performing Second delivery flow in Telesales channel, We have observed, Omnius is allowing to select new identification method in checkout.

Response body:
{code:java}
{"error":false,"data":[{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"Online","isDisabled":false},{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"Door","isDisabled":false},{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"Store","isDisabled":false},{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"DHLFilialident","isDisabled":false}]}{code}
Please find below screenshots:

1. Agent clicks on SECOND DELIVERY (Zweitversand) button.

!image-2024-05-16-19-08-58-897.png|width=379,height=283!

2. Created a valid shopping cart with selection of Hardware in shopping cart.

!image-2024-05-16-19-10-07-792.png|width=387,height=203!

3. Customer identification section is in editable mode.

!image-2024-05-16-19-11-28-632.png|width=534,height=281!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Agent logged in Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Agent loaded existing Customer which is eligible for second delivery.
 # Agent clicks on SECOND DELIVERY (Zweitversand) button and created a valid shopping cart
 # Agent reached to checkout page on Customer data section.
 # Verify Customer identification section.

Actual: Omnius allows to select new identification menthod in Kundenidentifikation section for second delivery use case.

Expected: *Agent should see ident method section in read only mode as Agent cannot change manually* and Agent should see error banner with text message in case same Original order ident method is not available in interface RetrieveIdentificationMethods response and sales flow should stop.

Reference story: OAF-101 OMNIUS : CHCK As an Agent, i wanted to validate ident method for Second Delivery Order/package from Original order,so that Agent will process same ident method without any change. - Vodafone Global Jira
column346: As currently Omnius is allowing to select new identification method in checkout, if agent select new identification method which will create another identification request for customer.

column937:
15/May/24 9:53 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

yes, currently the fix is almost ready after discussions with design team and Ketaki.

in this fix the 24 retry will not be in use anymore, instead the retry will be determined by the ogw_error_handler table.

it will decide how many times to retry, and how much time to wait between the calls.

for this flow the retry will be active for empty response from oneDMS or OGWERR-9900 error code return

for example:
this is a record from the table:

{
    "ERROR_CODE":"OGWERR-9900",
    "ERROR_CATEGORY":"Technical",
    "IGNORE_ERROR_IND":"N",
    "RETRYABLE_IND":"TRUE",
    "MAX_RETRY_TIMES":"3",
    "RETRY_WAIT_TIME":"10",
    "MAX_WAIT_TIME":null,
    "STATUS_TO_SET":null,
    "CHANNEL":"TELESALES",
    "SERVICE_CALL":"ASYNC",
    "SERVICE_NAME":"OneDMS"
}
so the flow will retry 3 times and the wait time will be 10 seconds between every try.;;;

column922:
18/Apr/24 12:36 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas with following outcome:
 * Values like "AccountCategory" in Omnius are derived from OGW: Here:- _AccountCategory_ in getCustomerResult for index search and _Region_ in retrieveCustomerInfo mode1 for LegacySearch.
 * As the ADDRESS REGION is in UM Area - it is treated as UM customer, even though he belongs to the VKD Stack

h4. _Possible SD option to be validated/proven:_ 
 * Derive customer stack from GlobalID prefix ("legacy stack")  instead of address region
 * IF improvements required as this is only known by OGW (Omnius can only see LK_ from linked customers) - e.g. introducing new attribute to indicate customers product stack:
 * CustomerSearch()
 * getCustomerDetails()
 * [@Mitra, Gaurab, External Vendor|mailto:gaurab.mitra@amdocs.com]: We should investigate if further interfaces have to be considered (To be discussed on next CR meeting)

[@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: To check UseCases in Omnius to be considered for an improvement

Further benefit: Omnius Performance increase If product stack information is directly provided by OGW 

 

So team is working on possible solution but will take some time ;;;

24/Jan/24 3:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  I was not creating any order, I am just scanning portal UI tool from time to time to find unidentified issues. And within this quality check I have found tickets with this error message. 

 

After some analysis I have identified, that it seems to be this scenario:

-> Search existing unitymedia customer and perform Move to VKD adress 

 

this is example Order ID from ACC1 - it failed with 2 sky tickets

One ticket because of invalid VPKN (issue is solved, please ignore that) and second sky ticket was for setpermission.


Unfortunately Sky ticket were cleared in between so I am not able to find my two tickets anymore..... But hopefully you can reproduce on your environment for a Move from Unity to VKD.

Seems like in this case the existing customer ID from unity is taken over, instead of recognizing that customer will get a new customer ID from VKD for Move scenario

 

Order ID 782545, Customer ID 1009755201 (initial customer before Move) 

!image-2024-01-24-11-21-17-927.png!

column1: OSF | CR716 Wave8.2 | ACC1 | Unitymedia | Error message is displayed in Access details if order placed in NE3 Address with self install =no
column41:
We tried placing an order with NE3 Address where Self install is no (ACC1)

in Access details we are getting the below error

({*}Your technical connection selection does not match){*}

!image-2023-12-15-18-50-55-105.png|width=406,height=222!

 

 

Steps to Recreate:

1)Take an address with NE3 and Self install=no(Example:51063,Köln ,Von-Galen-Str. 63) in unitymedia region

2)Select any of  the KIP Product(TV Will get added automatically)

3)checkout and move forward

4)check whether any error message is shown in Access Details

 

Actual: Error message is shown at access details page

Expected: No error message should be shown in Access details page 

Note:If we change the access details option to technician required for TV product then we are able to move forward without any issue
column346: Agent might get confused with the error message in connection selection and needs to use some workaround to be able to proceed (only NE3 Address where Self install is no is affected)
column591: Fixed - new requirements

column891: As a workaround the agent can trigger execution of the posting rules by selecting and deselecting any product.
column896:
21/Nov/23 6:51 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;Analysis results:

To prevent more issues related to [[OTF-902] KIPOPENEDMARKER not being sent in submit order xml || ADD and Drop Cable backend error - Vodafone Global Jira|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OTF-902] we improved the detection of empty packages in OSF to prevent the agent from entering the checkout with such.

In this case however the package is not empty as it contains VB4. As such our rule should not trigger if the posting rules were executed correctly after clicking the button to create the GigaKombi bundle.

This issue must be fixed by OSF - the posting must be executed after the bundle is created and a product (like VB4) is added to the package.;;;

column918:
13/Dec/23 4:42 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):
 * the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
 * the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is _any_ change to the TV package
 * after the bundle is created the TV package _is changed as it now contains VB4_
 * as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

*OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.* ;;;
column919:
14/Dec/23 1:55 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com] [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] 

 
Hari Shankar Malviya 
added a comment -
 
Hi Alexander/Simon,
 
 For extended shopping cart min max equal warning rules, there is not relation with cable post rule results or execution.
The rule which is problematic, is a max(0) rule and service to category rule. So if this rule’s service source expression evaluates to true than it will check if cart have max 0 number of products only from the target category. So if product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not part of the package then problematic rule service source expression will evaluate to true and further it will show warning if from target category we have more then 0 products in cart.;;;

column923:
14/Dec/23 4:54 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com], I am not sure if there was any more specific documentation (I will keep searching for a bit), but the following HLD already has a section:
|*Cable artifact rules*
 
The Cable Catalog and PLM colleagues have requested their own rules engine to be applied in the configurator. This is realised with a plugin development where Cable colleagues can upload their Rules Artifact as part of the PLM process. This Rules Artifact consists of the same Sales Rules (in PHP language/cable-speak) that is used currently in ECC front-ends. OMNIUS will share the full-shoppingcart (all packages) to the Rules Artifact, the rules artifact will process ruling, and return the shoppingcart object with modified cable orderlines in Kabel TV, KIP and KUD packages to be displayed in OMNIUS. The Rules Artifact will be called both before a product is selected (on show of configurator, pre-condition) {*}as well as after selecting a product (on adding to the shoppingcart, post-condition){*}. OMNIUS will not be able to have special GUI handling like for internal OMNIUS sales rules when using the Artifact.|

Highlighting added by me.

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/01%20V-HLD%20Vertical%20HLDs/HLD%202.0/V-HLD_01_Workpackage%201_Scenario%201c-v2%2018.docx]

 

From a slightly newer HLD:
|Apart from the Omnius compatibility rules for cable, specific precondition and postcondition rules from cable are also evaluated within the Cable Rules Artifact. *With each change in the configurator (for cable products) the Omnius rules and Cable rules artifact are evaluated in a loop, until a stable state is reached.* |

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_30%20HLD%20Wave%203_Product%20Catalogue-v2.11.docx]

column926:
05/Jan/24 4:31 PM;frederik.finckh@vodafone.com;Hi all, I have tried to reproduce this bug again, and verified once again that what Simon wrote in this comment is still true. I think it really comes down to the posting rules not being executed after the bundle rules changed the selection.
{quote}Simon Auch, Vodafone (External) added a comment - 13/Dec/23 12:12 PM

As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):

the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is any change to the TV package
after the bundle is created the TV package is changed as it now contains VB4
as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.
{quote};;;

column1: OSF Wave 8.1 ACC2 - ON HOLD OSIP-1359 Contract Summary: Price of old TV Product is missing (only OSF)
column41:
test environment: test1b /ACC2 Wave 8.1

Scenario: 
Existing Unitymedia cable customer with following inventory: legacy KIP Product (not Broadvision) and legacy TV Product (Code UMDKLM) orders GigaZuhause 1000 (Broadvision product) - Telesales 

Rabatt UMDTZBK is added --> this is correct / legacy TV product itself stays with "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service)

Fill in all mandatory information in checkout section and move until Contract Summary creation

Contract Summary OSF:
{color:#de350b}Price "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service" 0 Euro --> not ok, Price should be 20,99 Euro{color}

!image-2023-11-08-15-09-20-446.png|width=364,height=318!

If you see the contract summary for same order placed in other portals like ZHP und MHV the behavior and display on Contract Summary is correct (and they also use outputmanagement, so issue has to be on OSF side) :

Price 20,99 is displayed -> ok
!image-2023-11-08-15-10-53-135.png|width=453,height=129!

Test customer was 552907801

order was submitted from ZHP weborder 7836630

column896:
09/Nov/23 7:56 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;From what I can see in VkdGateway the price of the product is correctly returned as:

"nonStandardRate": 17.64, 

which with VAT makes ~20.99€.

The product itself however does not seem to indicate that it has a price nor a non standard rate, both of which should however not be necessary for unity inventory products.

It is noteworthy that the product itself has no price configured in the product setup, maybe the display in the contract summary of OSF does not work if it is an inventory product without a price (and without a non standard rate actually configured in the product setup)?

To me this sounds a) like an OSF issue and b) not like a BV issue.;;;

column1: OSF | ACC3 | ON HOLD Wave 8.1 | IMPROVEMENT CR to fix DSL Telesales orders are getting stuck at OnHold-PendingDSLShop
column41:
While performing today sanity we observed that DSL telesales orders are stuck at state OnHold-PendingDSLShop. so that orders are not getting submitted to backend. {color:#de350b}*This is only for ACC3*{color}

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Omnius Telesales channel

Select DSL Product

Proceed to checkout

Submit order

Track order in OGW

 

*Expected Result:*

Order confirmation by DSL shop should came from Tivano/Eshop

Order should submit to BE 

 

Test data : 
Order id :  428201  , Barcode : VDE5600000076

Order id : 428193  , Barcode: VDE5600000058
column346: DSL Orders are not getting submitted to backend in case we are changing the sequence on OGW side for OGW order ID
column591: delivery of CR804
column896:
25/Oct/23 12:14 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Defect to be kept ON-HOLD-- currently here the issue is that OGW is creating a BARCODE which can accept max 8 digits where the new sequence id which is changed for OGW order is is having 9 digits due to which when OGW is trying to search customer is CDM it counts the 8 digits starting from RHS where the last digit is ignored 
So in this case the new order id = 900000073 where while searching it is only calculating 73 ignoring all the 0 digits as they are null.
The last 9 digit =9 is been not counted at all as it only does counting until 8 digits which is 00000073 

To adapt these changes --we need to have a CR in OGW to implement the changes;;;

column41:
Testdata:
Test environment: ACC2

Test address: Von-Galen-Str. 63, 51063 Köln (ENV address) or Adlerstr. 6 40211 Düsseldorf Pempelfort (Any UM Address)

 

+Actual Result:+ access details are missing for TV Unity orders 

{+}Expected Result{+}: access details should be displayed for TV Unity orders

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 - create a new customer on ACC2 on any unity address ex:Adlerstr. 6 40211 Düsseldorf Pempelfort
 - click on "Produkte hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"

 - select any TV tariff, e. g.: Vodafone TV Connect 
 - click on the button "Weiter"
 - click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 - enter customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

-> Access details are not displayed, the should be displayed before the delivery details

 * which products exactly control the display of the tv access details in OSF?
 ** Is it only TECYESTV and TECNOTV or also products like VP0, 1V1?

 ** we have a list of ~80 test cases. Some of these are apparently not correct.
